title: crab puffs
directions: Mix well.
Spread on melba toast rounds, plain or sesame seed crackers.
Sprinkle with paprika and broil until very light brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans.
Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Ad eggs, shredded zucchini and water.
Mix to combine. Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and ground cinnamon.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: orange and lemon cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients except powdered sugar.
Add orange and lemon zest.
In a separate bowl, combine orange juice, lemon juice and milk.
Set aside to sour the milk.
Beat margarine and sugar at high speed until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternating, add one-third of flour mixture and one-third of milk mixture, beating well after each addition.
Bake at 350° in a greased pan for 45 to 55 minutes until golden brown. Cool for 10 minutes.
If desired, glaze cake or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mac 'n beef
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook meat and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup; add remaining ingredients. Heat through, stirring often.
Makes 8 servings.

title: country sausage
directions: To fresh ground pork add red pepper, sage and salt.
Mix well.

title: lentils and rice (imjadara)
directions: In 4 cups of water, boil lentils, diced onion and 4 tablespoons butter for 30 minutes.
Add fried onion in butter to lentil mixture.
Add rice and cook slowly until rice is done.
Add salt to taste.
Serves 6.
Very good with cabbage salad with Lebanese Salad Dressing.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Cut Twinkies in halves.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, goo side up.
Spoon pineapple over Twinkies (juice and all).
Spoon pudding on top of pineapple and spread evenly.
Slice bananas and strawberries.
Place on top of pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip. Chill if you have time.

title: shrimp and spaghetti
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed.
Cook green pepper, mushrooms and onions in margarine until tender.
Add with shrimp to sauce. Heat.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Mix in large saucepan, cherries, pineapple (both with juice), flour and sugar.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into the jello immediately after removing from stove.
Stir in food coloring for pinkish shade.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, add bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pulla(finnish coffee bread)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead well.
Allow dough to rise until double in size.
Knead again.
Roll out dough into 3 strips and braid them into 12-inch loaves.
Brush with beaten eggs immediately before baking.
Sprinkle with sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
(Brush with a little sugar water as soon as you remove the loaves from the oven.)

title: chuck's pineapple cheese ball
directions: Put cream cheese in small bowl.
Mix and soften 2 minutes. Add onion and green pepper.
Mix together well.
Drain pineapple well and add to mixture.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Enough for 1 loaf or two small loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked sweet ham
directions: Pierce ham thoroughly with a large fork.
Place in a large bowl or pot. Cover with Dr. Pepper. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Drain. Heat oven to 350°.
Put ham on rack.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Let cool.
Insert cloves.
Mix the reserved pineapple juice with sugar.
Spread thickly, fat side up.
Put pineapple on and hold with toothpicks.
Bake 30 minutes.
Prepare yams, potatoes and vegies.

title: apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over chopped apples and let set 20 minutes.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, allspice and salt.
Mix in eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add apples, sugar and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Serve with lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Cut both ends from can of corned beef hash.
Slice and brown in skillet.
Heat can of spinach and season.
Make white sauce. Place spinach on dish and make a nest in center.
Fill with white sauce and top with browned corned beef.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix all in bowl; seal and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients together into the blender, then mix well.

title: chicken and corn casserole
directions: Make a white sauce with the first 6 ingredients.
Add the sauce to the chicken and creamed corn.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Dot the top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
In a baking dish, layer the Tostitos, the ground beef and the cheese.
In a bowl, combine the other ingredients and pour over the cheese.
Put more grated cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In 20 quart
canner,
boil
stewing chicken with canner 1/2 full of water.
When
done,
save
water.
Pick
meat
off bones, then put meat
back
in canner with water.
Add College Inn chicken broth and fill
up rest of canner with water.
Add celery and carrots and boil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients including noodles;
no need to boil again.
Put in canning jars.
Pressure can
quarts
for
15 minutes and pints for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 18 quarts.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix
pudding and buttermilk.
Add drained oranges.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Break or crumble cookies and add to salad just prior to serving.

title: new orleans butter pralines
directions: Place 2 large parchment paper sheets on baking sheets (butter parchment sheets).
Set aside.
Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in a heavy, 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Stir briskly, until mixture loses its glossy sheen.
Working quickly, drop by teaspoons onto buttered paper.
Let cool completely.
Remove and store in airtight container.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sugar-free apple crisp
directions: Mix apples and raisins in casserole dish.
Mix oats, flour, cinnamon and margarine until crumbly.
Put on top of apples and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until apples are tender. May add sweetener to this also.
Serve warm.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Save a few crumbs for garnishing the top.

title: sweet lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in 2 gallons of water and lime overnight. Rinse well and cover with fresh water.
Soak 3 hours and then drain.
Cover with vinegar, sugar, salt, cloves, spice and celery seed.
Soak overnight.
Cook 40 minutes and then pack in jars.

title: strawberry mess
directions: Microwave for 2 minutes.
Mix as package says, using less water.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix together Ricotta cheese, sugar and eggs.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 baking pan.
Carefully spoon Ricotta mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° 60 to 65 minutes, or until done.
Cool on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Place first 8 items in a clean glass jar or bowl.
Bring sugar, vinegar and oil to a boil.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.
Stir a few times. Keeps about 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Add chicken.
Stir well.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed Town House crackers.
Drizzle melted butter over crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seeds over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).
Serve over rice.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Press fruit down in cup to make full cup.
Combine first 6 ingredients in skillet and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add nuts and Rice Krispies and mix well.
Form into balls the size of large walnuts and press down in coconut. Turn over and press other side in coconut.
Press to thickness desired.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: chocolate dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat cake mix (dry), margarine and 1 egg in large bowl on low speed until crumbly.
Press on bottom of pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 10 minutes.
Beat 2 eggs on high speed until foamy.
Beat in ice cream on speed until well mixed. Sprinkle chips over baked layer; pour ice cream mixture over chips.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: haystack butterscotch candy
directions: Put in double boiler the tidbits and melt, then add peanuts and noodles.
Stir until mixed, then drop over wax paper.
Makes about 45.

title: zesty bean dip
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, combine beans, seasoning mix and tomato.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon into serving bowl. Top with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
(Can be kept in fondue pot.)

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices. Season. Dredge in corn meal. Heat oil in heavy skillet. Add tomatoes and fry slowly until browned, turning once. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: jamboli
directions: Cook in big saucepan; add onion, celery, green pepper, garlic and margarine; cook for 15 minutes.
Add whole tomatoes, tomato paste, Polish sausage (cut up into bite size pieces) and Creole seasoning.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add bite size chicken and 1 teaspoon hot sauce; cook for 30 minutes.
Add 2 cups cooked rice and simmer all for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, leaving skins on.
Slice potatoes into wedges. Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brush potatoes with oil. Shake seasoned salt on potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.
Test to make sure they are done.

title: bing cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix in the blender the cherry juice, pineapple juice and softened cream cheese; set aside.
Whip the whipping cream.
Fold into cream cheese mixture the whipped cream, cherries, pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant; slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Fry on both sides in oil in large skillet, until tender.
Add more oil if necessary. Drain on paper towels.
Place 1/2 eggplant on bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of Ricotta cheese on top. Combine paste and water; mix.
Pour 1/2 over Ricotta cheese. Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle 1/2 over layers in pan.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Combine other ingredients except chips.
Heat thoroughly.
In large casserole dish, layer with chips, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: grandmother ruby's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Beat eggs and add sugar and flour.
Add melted butter and chocolate mixture and vanilla, then nuts.
Pour into shallow, well buttered pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until done.
Cut into squares and dust with powdered sugar.
These squares are cake-like rather than chewy.

title: cranberry-nut coffee cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
In a separate bowl, mix together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Add almond extract; mix well.
Pour 1/2 batter in a greased and floured tube pan.
Spread evenly to cover bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 cranberry sauce over batter.
Add remaining batter, then top with cranberry sauce. Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Leave in pan for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate buttercream frosting
directions: Cream margarine and shortening together.
Add vanilla. Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry. Add cocoa and milk and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wash and cut broccoli into spears. Boil spears in 1/2 cup water for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain water when done.
Line pan with broccoli.
Layer of chicken.
In bowl, mix soup and cream; pour evenly over chicken cubes.
Top with chicken. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: energy-packed granola
directions: In large bowl, combine oats, coconut, almonds, sunflower seeds and wheat germ.
Combine honey and oil; stir into oat mixture. Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook oat mixture at High for 10 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Stir in fruits.
Remove to another pan to cool.
Stir occasionally during cooling to prevent lumping.
Store in tightly covered jars or plastic bags.
Makes 6 cups.

title: angel hair pasta
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in pan; cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Set aside; keep warm.
Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Place in a bowl.
Add pine nut mixture and toss.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Keep refrigerated. Serves 8.

title: veggie salad
directions: Mix all together and leave to marinate overnight.

title: deep fried wonton
directions: Combine
meat,	shoyu, sherry, sesame oil, salt, ginger and chives
or	green
onion
in
a frying pan and saute over medium heat
until
meat
is
cooked.
Place
about
a half a teaspoon of meat mixture in the center of a wonton skin.
Fold in
half to make a rectangle.
Fold in half again, lengthwise. Bring
the ends of the narrow rectangle together and press the corners
of	the first
fold
together, sealing with a dab of diluted
egg mixture.
(The
finished
wonton
looks
like
a nurse's cap.) Deep fry until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Saute chicken until brown. Remove chicken and place in baking dish.
Add onion and pepper to remaining margarine and cook until onion is clear.
Turn off heat and add mushrooms and liquid.
Add sour cream and chestnuts.
Pour over chicken; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together, except noodles; turn into a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with noodles.
Bake until bubbly (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Serve warm.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix together Jello and crushed pineapple.
Bring to a boil. Let cool.
Add Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Stir well and pour into baked pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator for a few hours before serving.
Enough for a 10-inch pie.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Mix in flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate morsels.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Peel and slice green apples.
Pour sugar over apples and let sit.
Sift flour two times; add baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Add to apples with beaten eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add chopped nuts. Mix until smooth.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with dollop of whip cream and a dash of cinnamon.

title: pie topping
directions: Put in top of double boiler.
Beat with mixer until mixed good.
Place over boiling water and beat until thickened.
Remove from heat and beat until stands in peaks, adding vanilla.
Pile on pie.

title: calico beans
directions: Cut bacon and brown with beef and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Drain 1/2 liquid from lima beans.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered.
This can be made in a crock-pot and left to simmer.

title: creamy scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs lightly with cream, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a very large frying pan, pour in egg mixture.
Cook slowly, stirring until almost set.
Fold in hot white sauce while eggs are still creamy.
Keep hot in very low oven (220°) or place over hot water on top of stove.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley if desired. Serves 24.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Shake mix and potatoes together in a sealed plastic bag.
Bake according to potato instructions.
Serve with Chile Dip.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion and pepper in olive oil; add all other ingredients and simmer 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: date fruit salad
directions: Mix raisins, apples, nuts and dates real good, then add mayonnaise and sugar.
Toss together real good.

title: hot mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Pour half of batter into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Arrange drained peppers on the batter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of cheese over peppers and batter.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cranberry crunch
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Melt butter in microwave with Saran Wrap.
Add that to dry ingredients mixture.
Spread cranberries on the bottom of an ungreased baking pan.
Cut and core apples.
Spread over the cranberries.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Pat down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Wipe mushrooms to clean.
Remove stems.
Combine stems, dill, salt and pepper to taste and cream cheese.
Pack into mushroom caps.
Place on a cookie sheet and broil until lightly browned. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve warm.

title: pork chops - sweet-sour
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a bag.
Rinse chops in cold water and shake one at a time in bag.
Brown chops in melted shortening or Pam in skillet.
Add pineapple juice and vinegar.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and cook over low
heat about 30 minutes. Remove chops and keep warm.
If you desire additional gravy, add remaining flour mixture to pan and stir with some orange juice until thickened.
Gravy is good on sweet or white potatoes, boiled or mashed.

title: maple zucchini squares
directions: Bake in 11 x 15 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: In saucepan, cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in flour; blend well.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, sausage, water, bay leaves, thyme, salt, basil, red pepper, pepper, uncooked rice and shrimp.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and cook over medium heat.
Stir frequently for 10 to 15 minutes until rice and shrimp are done.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim off fat; slice meat with grain and thin.
Place meat in shallow pan.
Combine other ingredients and pour over meat. Marinate overnight.
Preheat oven to 125°.
Lay strips on oven rack in single layer; put foil on bottom of oven to catch drippings.
Leave oven door open a crack.
Test occasionally. Bake 8 to 12 hours, until chewy.

title: marvelous make-ahead salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green pepper, celery, peas and onion in large salad bowl.
Reserve center slices of egg for garnish.
Layer remaining egg slices and half the cheese over vegetables.
Spread dressing over salad, sealing to edge.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Chill, covered, for 2 hours to overnight.
Garnish with reserved egg slices and parsley.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: lime pie
directions: For Crust:
Combine butter, crumbs and sugar.
Press into pie pan to form a crust.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes to set.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together sugar, milk, margarine and water; heat.
After heated, add marshmallows.
After marshmallows are melted, add vanilla. Mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Mix well.
Slice both layers of cake. Spread mixture over.
Replace layers, icing with Duncan Hines dark chocolate frosting.

title: eggs mcmommy
directions: Toast English muffin.
Poach egg in small saucepan or microcook in small dish.
If cooking egg in microwave, be sure to top with 1 teaspoon of milk and prick yolk with fork.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: salmon puff
directions: In saucepan, mix bread crumbs, mustard and milk.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Flake salmon with fork and stir in. Beat in egg yolks.
In large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff. Slowly fold in salmon mixture.
Turn into buttered casserole dish. Place casserole dish into pan of water and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: country goulash
directions: Boil potatoes that have been cut into small pieces, drain. Cook hamburger and sausage together.
Drain off grease.
Mix hamburger, sausage, corn, tomatoes, drained potatoes and barbecue sauce.
Simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: simple cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and butter; add salt, pepper and flour.
Roll thin.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: dessert squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk.
Add milk.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dream salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice, crushed pineapple and pie cherries.
Chill.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients in pan to boiling, stirring often. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes to thicken. Brush on meats during last 20 minutes of broiling or grilling.
Makes 2 cups.

title: refrigerator spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Place in airtight covered container and store in refrigerator.
As needed, spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400°
about 20 minutes.
The dough can be kept a week and remember, no rising time is required.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Rivel the first 3 ingredients together.
Take out 1 cupful of the rivels for on top, then add egg, sour milk and soda to the rest of rivels.
Stir all together, then sprinkle 1 cup of crumbs on top.
Bake at 375°.

title: no cook chocolate dessert
directions: Mix milk and instant pudding mix in large bowl. Let stand until pudding sets (approximately 5 minutes).
Fold in Cool Whip. Leaving graham crackers whole as possible, layer on bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Next, layer half the pudding mixture, then another layer of crackers and layer on rest of pudding.
Top with layer of crackers.

title: nellie's honey french salad dressing
directions: Mix in a blender the ingredients except salad oil.
When well blended, add salad oil.
Great on spinach, regular lettuce salads and with fruit.

title: easy doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, cream and buttermilk.
Sift and add flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Chill dough before rolling out.
Fry at 375°.
If you wish, dip some doughnuts in powdered sugar and some in granulated sugar.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Combine green beans, wax beans, kidney beans, vinegar, green onions, NutraSweet, oil, basil, garlic, salt and pepper in a large nonmetallic bowl.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve chilled.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix well; roll into small balls and chill for a short time. Dip into a mixture of 6 ounce package of chocolate bits melted with a small square of paraffin wax.
Store in a cool place.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, soy sauce and brown sugar. Marinate the chicken breasts in this mixture overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, bake chicken at 350° or until done. Then, stir fry peppers and onions until translucent.
Smother cooked chicken with peppers and onions.
Cover with Provolone cheese and bake until brown and cheese is melted.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 6 ingredients. Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter; mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: corn cob jelly(sometimes called poor man's jelly)
directions: Wash corn cobs and cut into 4-inch lengths.
Place in container and add 2 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil slowly for 30 minutes.
Strain the juice.
Measure 3 cups of juice into a large saucepan.
Add pectin and bring to a boil.
Add sugar and bring to boiling point again.
Boil 5 minutes.
Skim, then pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: sauce piquante
directions: Boil chicken until meat comes off the bone, remove from pot. Add onion, celery, 4 cloves garlic and bell pepper to drippings in pot and saute in chicken fat until clear.
Add deboned chicken, tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, red pepper and sugar.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add 4 cloves garlic, onion tops, mushrooms and parsley. Add water; more water may be necessary, add according to desired thickness.
Cook slow on low heat 3 to 4 hours.
Approximately 20 minutes before serving, add crabmeat and shrimp.
Season to taste. Serve over rice.

title: cheeseburger skillet dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, brown meat with onion.
Drain. Stir in vegetables, ketchup, water, mustard and garlic powder. Cook until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Mix in macaroni and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: open faced raisin pie
directions: Mix all together, except the egg whites.
Last mix in the well beaten egg whites.
Pour in uncooked pie crust.
Makes one large pie.
Bake slow (275°) until a well formed crust is on top and it is well browned.

title: craisin pasta
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, over medium- high heat, heat oil. Add pork cubes, cook and stir 2 or 3 minutes, until browned. Add broth and bring to a boil.
Add pasta, zest, and craisins. Cover and cook about 10 minutes until pasta is al dente.
While pasta is cooking, remove outer wrapping from the frozen broccoli, place broccoli in microwave oven and microwave on high for 3 minutes. Cut broccoli florets into bite size pieces.

Add broccoli florets to cooked pasta, continue cooking pasta mixture uncovered until liquid is reduced and sauce is thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in salt, pepper and walnuts. Serve with cheese.

title: italian-style burgers
directions: Stir together bread crumbs, milk, onion, parsley, Parmesan cheese, garlic and pepper.
Add meat; mix well.
Shape into 4 patties 3/4-inch thick.
Place patties on unheated rack of a broiler pan (or grill).
Cook 6 minutes; turn for 6 to 8 more minutes until done.
Top each burger with a slice of tomato; sprinkle with oregano and Mozzarella.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes more. Makes 4 servings at 202 calories each.

title: orange jello salad or dessert
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with crushed pineapple in pan and bring to a full boil.
Add next 2 ingredients and let cool. Beat cream cheese and add to cooled mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 hour until Jell-O starts to set.
Fold in a large carton Cool Whip (beat with mixer at low speed).
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, butter, brown sugar and salt.
Keep 1 cup for
topping.
Press
in
9 x 13-inch pan and cover with sliced apples.

title: microwave caramel corn(fast, cheap, easy)
directions: Put popped corn in a large, brown paper sack.
(I sit it in the sink.)
Combine all ingredients, except for the soda and popcorn, in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish.
Cook at full power.
As soon as it starts to boil, stop the microwave and stir.
Then boil at full power for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in the soda.
It is very hot! Pour this mixture over the popped corn and stir until it is well coated.
Return the brown sack to the microwave on full power for another 1 1/2 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water, margarine and vanilla.
Blend well with mixer or spoon.
Pour into 1 quart loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine butter,
sugar and eggs.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Blend
in sour cream.
Sift flour with soda and baking
powder
into the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: orange sweet potato bowl
directions: Cook potatoes or yams in boiling salt water about 15 minutes, or just until tender.
Drain them; shake pan gently over low heat 2 or 3 minutes to dry potatoes.
Mash potatoes well.
Stir in butter, brown sugar and orange juice, then whip with fork until fluffy.
Spoon into serving dish; garnish with fresh orange sections and parsley, if you wish.

title: sour cream pound cake(won first place blue ribbon state fair 1993)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the butter and sugar, beating until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating to blend.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream; mix well on low speed.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in butter, then in crumb mix.
Place in a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350 degree oven.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together; top with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put zucchini, onions and pickling salt in large bowl.
Mix well and let stand overnight.
Next day, drain and rinse well in cold water and drain again.
Put in large kettle with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally 30 minutes or to desired thickness you want.
Then put in pint jars.
Process 5 minutes.

title: betsy's english toffee icebox dessert
directions: Combine pecans and vanilla wafer crumbs.
Spread half on the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Melt the chocolate in a small pan and set aside to cool.
Cream butter.
Add sugar, mixing well and then egg yolks.
Beat until well blended.
Add chocolate.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the chocolate mixture. Spread over the crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill 24 hours.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Serves 8 or 9.

title: homemade cheese danish
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, lemon juice and vanilla. Take 1 package of crescent rolls and unroll it (do not separate pieces) and place on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling mixture on top.
Cover with second pack of crescent rolls.
Lay whole sheet unseparated on top of filling.
Brush with egg white and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; add nuts if desired.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350°.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: Combine water, milk, honey and oil (if used).
Heat to lukewarm (125°).
Stir together yeast, 2 1/2 cups flour and salt. Add milk mixture and beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour. Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl; cover with damp towel.
Let rise until double.
Punch down dough.

title: low calorie cheesecake
directions: Mix all together in blender or food processor.
Pour into an 8-inch pan and refrigerate.
Makes four servings.

title: sweet-sour beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onion and cook until clear.
Add vinegar, sugar and bean liquid.
Thicken in skillet and add to beans.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together ingredients; roll into small balls.
Refrigerate several hours, until they are good and firm, then dip into dipping chocolate.
Use toothpicks to dip; only cover 3/4 of each piece of candy.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with chips.

title: john wayne's corn chowder
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons butter until they are tender and translucent.
Add the corn, potatoes, chicken broth and herbs. Simmer for 25 minutes.
Puree the soup in a blender.
Return to pot; simmer before serving.
Add the cream and butter.
Check for seasoning.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and form into a roll or ball.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: grandma's sweet chili sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, cook down tomatoes, onions and peppers until reduced over medium heat.
While reducing, simmer the remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
When vegetables are reduced to desired consistency, mix in the remaining sauce from the small saucepan.
Cook over low heat.
When water separated out to the top, it's done!

title: veal scaloppine with mushrooms
directions: Place veal between sheets of waxed paper and pound with a cleaver or a small heavy skillet until 1/4-inch thick.
Be careful not to tear the veal.
Dip the meat into the seasoned flour, shaking off the excess.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix by hand lightly to avoid mashing cherries.
Cook in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm to the touch.

title: creeping crust cobbler
directions: Melt butter in dish; mix flour and sugar.
Add milk.
Pour batter over butter.
Pour fruit in center.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Put in 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until heated.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add nuts and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: ree's rhode island beans
directions: Mix kidney beans, B&M beans, lima beans, tomatoes, onion, sausage and bacon together.
Add to mixture brown sugar, mustard, garlic powder and vinegar.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: In a large mixer bowl, mash potatoes until smooth.
Add cream cheese in small pieces, and butter and beat well until cheese and butter are melted.
Add sour cream to milk and egg mixture with the salt and pepper, add to potato mixture and beat until fluffy. Place in a 9-inch greased casserole and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated oven at 350° until lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: pineapple bakeless cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and mix well.
Add egg, mix well. Add evaporated milk and pineapple.
Fold in pecans.
Alternate layers of wafers with pineapple mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish. Should make 2 layers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill for 12 hours or more.
Serves 8.

title: hot hominy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in baking dish.
Sprinkle grated fat-free cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: favorite waffles
directions: With rotary beater, beat eggs well. Beat in milk until high, thick and foamy. Then beat in drys, then melted shortening. Batter may be stored in covered container in refrigerator for about 3 days; do not stir more than necessary when baking stored batter.

title: hardy's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and oil; mix well.
Let set overnight in fridge.
Can be kept several days.
Bake in preheated 450° oven.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers all in blender and liquify.
Strain and use juice only.
Add juice, vinegar and 6 cups sugar.
Bring to boil; remove from heat and skim top.
Return to heat and add Certo and red or green food coloring.
Bring to hard boil for 1 minute.
Jar and seal.

title: yummy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon in oven on broiling pan (at 400 degrees) until crisp (save grease).
Drain beans of liquid and remove pork from them.
Chop onions (fine).
Mix above ingredients together (mix well).
Add 8 Tbsp. of bacon grease.
Mix well again.

title: ice cream wafers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt and vanilla. Drop by 1/2 teaspoonful on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Edges will be slightly brown when done.
Cool and store in airtight container to retain crispness.
Be sure to give them room to spread.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix
onion,
cheese, soup, sour cream, milk, nearly all the butter
(saving a little) and hash browns.	Pour into a 13 x 9-inch
greased
pan.
Sprinkle
corn
flakes
across top of casserole and then pour remaining butter over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Add garlic, tomato paste and liquid.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and a pinch of nutmeg, cayenne pepper and allspice.
Add Parmesan cheese and cook slowly about 30 minutes in covered saucepan.
Add sherry last few minutes.
Serve over broccoli or asparagus.

title: shrimp vermouth
directions: To raw shrimp, sprinkle with K-Paul's seafood seasoning for a few hours with a little cayenne pepper.
Saute shrimp in a little butter cooked on low.
In large skillet, cook shallots, thyme, basil, garlic and vermouth for 5 minutes.
Add cream and cook until thick.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Stir in shrimp and crab meat; heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice or angel hair pasta. Serves 6 to 8.

title: special k bars
directions: Heat corn syrup and
sugar.
Remove
from
heat and add peanut butter.
Mix in Special
K	cereal	and press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips. Use as frosting.
Chill.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients into shaker jar.
Shake until blended. Serve chilled over tossed greens.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook sweet potatoes in boiling salted water just until tender, about 5 to 8 minutes (do not overcook). Drain; toss with the lemon juice. In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, orange juice, honey, orange peel, ginger, salt and nutmeg. Add the warm potatoes, celery and dates. Toss to coat well. Cover and chill. Before serving, gently stir in the pecans.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Add water, sugar and margarine to fruit.
Place crust mixture on top of blackberries and bake at 350° until crust is brown, about 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soak yeast in lukewarm water; pour scalded milk over lard, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Then add yeast, eggs and flour.
Beat dough about 5 minutes or until it blisters.
Place in covered bowl in refrigerator.
Take out about 3 1/2 hours before using.
Form into rolls.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: saltwater taffy
directions: Butter the sides of a 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar, corn syrup, 1 cup water and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking to 265° (hard ball stage), without stirring (mixture should boil gently over entire surface).
Remove from heat; stir in butter or margarine.
Add flavoring and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Cool about 20 minutes or until easily handled.

title: savory chicken stew
directions: In Dutch oven, place oil and heat to medium-high. Add chicken and cook until brown on all sides.
Remove and set aside.
To drippings, add all vegetables except cabbage.

Cook, stirring about 10 minutes until lightly brown. Remove and set aside. Return chicken, 2 cups water, bouillon cubes, salt, marjoram, thyme, pepper and sage. Cover and cook about 20 minutes. Return vegetables to pan.
Place cabbage over all. Cover and cook about 20 to 25 minutes longer until done.
Take out chicken and vegetables. Set aside.
Place cornstarch in bowl with 1 tablespoon water.
Mix.
Stir into pan juices until slightly thickened. Return chicken and veggies to pan.
(I take chicken off the bone.) Heat through. Serve over noodles.

title: cornbread
directions: Put grease or oil in iron skillet.
Heat in 450° oven until very hot.
Meanwhile, beat egg well; stir in buttermilk.
Just before skillet is ready, stir in enough corn meal to be medium thick.
When skillet is hot, pour 1/2 hot oil in batter.
Stir in well.
Pour cornbread mixture into skillet.
Bake until dry looking and brown (about 20 minutes).

title: texas pecan candy cake
directions: Combine cherries, pineapple and dates.
Sprinkle with flour and toss to coat well.
Add pecans and coconut.
Toss, then add milk and stir to mix.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and place in 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and wrap in foil and refrigerate 2 weeks.

title: bonnie's dessert
directions: Mix the flour, butter and nuts together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 12 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on the cooled crust.
Spread the cooled pudding over the cream cheese mixture and top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Boil chicken (or do in crock-pot) and debone.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Add cream cheese and half of melted butter. Mix well, then spread on crescent rolls; fold.
Roll in bread crumbs which have been mixed with remaining half of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: red potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain and cut into bite size pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp and reserve.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until soft.
Pour onions and drippings over hot potatoes.
Add oil, vinegar, parsley, red onion, celery and crumbled bacon.
Toss gently, but thoroughly.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Melt jello in hot water; add dash of salt.
Cut cucumber in half and remove seed.
Grate cucumber and onion and set aside. Beat cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in jello and remaining ingredients.
Congeal.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese.
Add tuna, soup, milk and seasoning.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place the rice in
a
two quart baking dish.
Add soup, celery and water.	Mix
well.
Place
pieces of raw chicken in mixture. Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown onion and meat in margarine.
Mix cornstarch and seasoning into tomato sauce.
Add sauce to meat mixture; stir well. When mixture bubbles and thickens, add cheese by thirds. When all cheese is melted, keep warm and start dipping cubed French or garlic bread.

title: firecracker casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until done; drain.
Add chili powder, cumin and salt.
Stir well.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Put meat mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pam-sprayed casserole dish.
Layer beans, tortillas and cheeses over meat mixture.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Cover casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: holiday taco dip
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together and spread in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Layer the rest of the ingredients in order.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 2 rolls and chill overnight.
Slice and bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch glass baking dish.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except 7-Up.
Just before serving, add 7-Up.
Pour over crushed ice.
Use different flavor Kool-Aid for occasions.
Makes about 40 cups.

title: lemon love
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg whites with electric mixer until frothy.
Add pecan halves.
Stir until coated with egg whites.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add to pecans and mix well.
Spread on buttered (or oleo) cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chopped chicken and eggs in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Mix soup, broth, salt and pepper together; pour over chicken.
In separate bowl, mix buttermilk, flour and margarine together.
Pour over chicken mixture; do not stir.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: frito chili pie
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups of corn chips in a baking dish.
Arrange chopped onion and half the grated cheese over the chips.
Pour heated chili over the onion and cheese.
Top with the remaining chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together butter, cream cheese, and powdered sugar in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix together milk, instant pudding, and Cool Whip; then mix with first mixture.
In large dish, layer 1/2 inch layer of crushed Oreos and then mixture.
Repeat layers and top with Oreo cookies.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 8-inch square casserole and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, uncovered.
Serve warm or hot with crackers.

title: dave's favorite baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients into large crock-pot.
Turn temperature to low and cook for 10 hours.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in oleo until clear.
Add roast beef and cook about 5 minutes. Stir in soups, water and sauces. Pour into casserole.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant and cut in finger lengths. Soak in salted water 1 hour.
Drain and dry thoroughly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Dredge with flour.
Dip in beaten egg and water mixture and roll in crumbs.
Fry in deep, hot fat (385°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Lay flank steak in shallow pan or bowl.
Tenderize as per directions on bottle.
Crush garlic cloves into oil.
Add lemon juice to oil.
Let stand 15 minutes to flavor.
Pour over steak, turning occasionally.
Let stand 4 hours at room temperature. Preheat broiler or outside grill.

Broil, turning once or twice, until medium rare, about 6 to 8 minutes or until doneness desired. Slice thinly in 1/3-inch slices at 45° angle against the grain. Serve with a platter of buttered toast.
Use any juice for dipping.
Excellent for next day cold sandwiches.

title: frosty cranberry mold
directions: Drain cranberry sauce and pineapple; reserve liquid.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Bring liquid to a boil and add Jell-O. Chill until partially set.
Beat softened cream cheese and salad dressing together until fluffy.
Add partially set Jell-O to mixture.
Fold this mixture into already whipped topping.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until surface is set (20 minutes).

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
In buttered casserole (8 x 12-inch), layer half the carrots and half the cheese; repeat layers.
Top with sauteed onions and cover casserole generously with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soak yeast in water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Put salt, fat and 1/2 cup sugar in large bowl.
Pour on boiling water.
Stir well. Cool.
Add the yeast and beaten eggs.
Beat in 4 cups of flour. Work in the rest of flour.
Put in large container.
Cover and store in refrigerator approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keeps 1 week.

title: best banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into a greased bread pan. Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.	Add complete jar of peanut butter and mix until peanut butter is melted.
Pour immediately over the 6 cups of corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool and enjoy.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen, depending on size of cookies.

title: mom's sour cream cabbage
directions: Place in a saucepan the cabbage, vinegar, sugar, salt and water.
Cook for 10 minutes and put in the oleo or butter and sour cream.
Serve hot.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Chill! Press pieces of dough quite thin into small fancy forms or tiny muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove gently. Serve as cookies or fill with fruit and whipped cream.
Makes 6 dozen.
Recipe originally from Norway.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix water and sugar; heat until clear.
Add pineapple, orange and lemon juice.
Freeze mixture.
Large top plastic containers are best; example: Cool Whip containers.
Let thaw until it can be chopped in small pieces.
Add ginger ale.
Serves about 50 people.

title: cider sip
directions: Mix and chill.
Great if partially frozen and served slushy. Always stir before serving.

title: harvest waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Prepare tangy dressing and reserve.
Core and dice apples.
Combine apples, pineapple, celery and nuts.

title: sunday delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: onion mushroom chuck roast
directions: Line a baking dish with aluminum foil big enough to wrap around roast.
Place roast on foil.
Sprinkle soup mix on top of roast.
Pour mushroom soup on top of this.
Wrap the foil tightly around the roast to prevent any steam from escaping.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours.
This makes its own gravy and is very good.
Bake at 350°.

title: lemon-herb chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put chicken breast in mixture and let set overnight or at least 6 hours.
Cook over grill or in broiler oven.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together potatoes, cheese, sour cream, soup, onion, 1/3 cup of butter, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Pour into buttered shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining melted butter with corn flakes; sprinkle over mixture. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: beef-onion rice mix
directions: Bring 2 3/4 cups water to a boil in medium saucepan.
Add 1 tablespoon butter or margarine (optional).
Add rice blend and return to boil.
Cover and simmer over medium-low heat 15 to 18 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: venison vegetable medley
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet.
Cook bacon pieces in skillet and then place in large 2 handled pot, Dutch oven or soup pot.
Brown deer meat in skillet in small batches, sprinkling with pepper. Add to soup pot.
In skillet saute onions, carrots and celery, sprinkling with sugar to caramelize slightly.
Add to soup pot. Add beef broth and wine to skillet and bring to boil, scraping up brown bits.
Reduce heat; swirl in butter, jelly and thyme.
Cook for a minute more.
Pour over meat in soup pot and simmer gently on low heat.
Add garlic, potatoes and parsley.
When vegetables and meat are nearly done, add tomatoes and simmer.
Do not thicken broth.
Serve with hearty bread or garlic bread for a filling but slightly different stew.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and salt to a boil. Add cabbage, onions and pimento and juice.
Remove from heat. Place in gallon jar and let stand for 24 hours.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Preheat skillet to 350°. Add butter and oil. When oil begins to smoke, add half the cabbage. Add the onions, bell peppers, celery and vegetable magic. Cook stirring occasionally, until vegetables begin to stick, about 8 to 9 minutes. Add 1/2 cup of stock and scrape the bottom of the skillet. Add the remaining cabbage. Mix well, cover and cook stirring once or twice until the second addition of the cabbage is fork tender, about 7 or 8 minutes. Add the remaining stock only if the liquid in the skillet evaporates completely and the cabbage is in danger of scorching.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Allow meat to steep in marinade for 2 hours.
Do not marinate in a metal pan; ingredients could react (especially to copper).
Place marinaded steaks on hot grill and cook to desired doneness.

title: fillmore street oatmeal pie
directions: Partially bake crust.
Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, syrup, vanilla and juice.
Stir in oats.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: fruit cake(no bake icebox)
directions: Add milk to vanilla wafers; add other ingredients and mix well (hands work best). Place into a mold, wrap and store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: puppy chow (for people)
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chips and margarine in microwave or on top of stove.
Pour mixture over cereal and toss to coat. Toss 10x sugar over cereal until coated (use more or less sugar as needed).

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add measured liquid. Add sherbet by spoonful, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges, reserving a few for garnish.
Pour into serving bowl or individual serving dishes.
Chill until set, at least 1 hour.
Makes about 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: filled coffee cake
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients into butter and blend well.
Blend in well beaten eggs, mixed with milk.
Blend in vanilla and beat just to mix.
Pour 1/2 batter in well-greased and floured large loaf pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of filling.
Add rest of batter and top with filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: grilled asparagus(from cooking light magazine)
directions: Prepare grill.	Note:
may use grill pan on stove.
Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Combine all ingredients except cooking spray in a large zip top plastic bag.
Seal and marinate for 30 minutes.
Remove asparagus from bag and discard marinade.
Place asparagus on grill rack coated with cooking spray.	Grill 5 minutes on each side or until asparagus is done.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine sugar, dry milk and cocoa in a large bowl.
Store in an airtight container.

title: white mountain cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Fold in nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes and margarine and cover top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole ii
directions: Blend beaten egg and soups. Add bread crumbs and chicken. Season to taste. Pour into casserole. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake 1 hour at 350°. May serve with mushroom soup gravy if desired.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and cheese on top.
In a saucepan, heat soup, milk and cream cheese until melted.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: dad's vegetable soup
directions: Cook each vegetable separately until almost done.
Mix all ingredients together and cook for 10 minutes.
Place in sterile pint canning jars and hot water bath for 1 hour.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and butter; pack in 8 x 12-inch baking dish and set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Top with dressing of:

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar and add 7-Up. Cook until real thick. Remove from heat and add 1/2 package strawberry jello. Let cool. Fold in strawberries (unsweetened). Top with whipped cream.

title: hobo lunch(individual)
directions: You will need square of aluminum foil.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Crush strawberries.
Stir in sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes. Boil water and Sure-Jell 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir into fruit and sugar mixture.
Continue stirring 3 minutes.
Ladle into containers.
Set at room temperature for 24 hours.
Store in freezer.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Roll in balls or drop from a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for about 8 minutes.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients, salt to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Serve with sour cream, optional.)
This is great with fruit salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon twist coffeecake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix 1 3/4 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine milk, water and 1/4 cup margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120°).
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat.
Stir in raisins and enough flour to make stiff dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic.
Roll out each half to a 12-inch square.
Brush with melted butter.

title: spareribs
directions: Mix the soy sauce, salt, 4 tablespoons brown sugar and flour. Marinate ribs in the mixture for half an hour or longer.
Fry the ribs in oil until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and let meat simmer until tender.
Slice turnips and carrots thinly and let stand in a little salt.
Add to the spareribs before serving.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with fork until dates are coated with flour.
Stir in 1 cup warm water; do not overmix.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs and butter.
Keep 1/4 cup of bread crumbs for topping.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Roll into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet until golden brown.
Roll into powdered sugar while warm.
May be frozen for future use.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jam
directions: Cook sugar, rhubarb and strawberries until rhubarb is soft. Stir in jello well.
Jar and freeze.

title: easy grape jelly
directions: Boil 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and put through a sieve to remove seeds and skins.
Bring liquid to a rolling boil.
Fill jars and top off with wax.
You may store it on shelf or in freezer.

title: sausage-cornbread dressing
directions: Soak cornbread and sandwich bread in chicken broth and water in a large bowl about 10 minutes; stir until liquid is absorbed. Saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Add sausage and cook over low heat until sausage is browned; drain. Add sausage mixture, eggs and pepper to bread mixture; stir well. Spoon dressing into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly browned. Makes 8 servings.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir once. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours and high, 5 to 6 hours.

title: green pig salad
directions: Thaw peas, but do not cook.
Combine with onion and celery. Fold in sour cream.
Add bacon and nuts.
Let chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: grilled pesto chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, together well.
Brush mixture on chicken breasts with pastry brush.
Place on foil and grill on low for 10 minutes each side.
Take off foil and grill to brown a little on each side.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and sour cream; cook until thick.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size peices.
Mix all ingredients. Reserve 1/2 cup noodles.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased casserole dish. Bake uncovered 40 minutes at 325°. During last 5 minutes sprinkle reserved noodles over top.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and add graham cracker crumbs, sugar, vanilla and peanut butter; mix well.
Add nuts.
Roll into teaspoon size balls.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and set in refrigerator for about 30 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix chili sauce, grape jelly and onion in a large pan over low heat until simmering.
Mix remainder of ingredients well.
Roll meat in one-inch diameter balls.
Drop one at a time in the sauce. Cover and cook on low heat for one and one half (1 1/2) hours. Makes approximately 90 meat balls.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir all of the first 5 ingredients together and cook in a black frying pan, stirring constantly.
Cook until peanuts turn brown, about 10 minutes.
Just before you take off the stove, add baking soda.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet and spread thin. Break into pieces when cool.

title: grilled marinated turkey steaks
directions: Have butcher cut turkey breast in half lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 1-inch thick steaks, resembling pork chops. Combine soy sauce with remaining ingredients.
Pour over turkey. Cover.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Remove from marinade.
Grill, covered with lid, for 8 to 10 minutes on each side.

title: brownies
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cover with Saran and let set in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes until fork-tender.
Drain and mash along with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Scoop onto pineapple rings and top with marshmallows and 1/2 a cherry.
Heat at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: best chip cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients together; beat with electric mixer until creamy.
Add flour and soda; mix with a large spoon.
Then add 1 to 1 1/2 cups chocolate or peanut butter chips or you can also use M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafood or chicken fettucini
directions: Saute vegetables in butter 15 minutes.
Add half and half, cheese (small chunks) and flour.
Cook sauce slowly for 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and Cajun spices to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Soak chicken breasts with chopped onions and celery.
Cut into small pieces and mix all ingredients and place in pan.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing and butter.
Cover chicken casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes and then uncover; brown until desired. Fabulous!!

title: egg noodle and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles and drain, then wash noodles.
Put hamburger, peppers and onion in pan and cook until brown.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix tomatoes, sugar, pepper, salt,
hot sauce and Del Monte Sloppy Joes.
Put all together and simmer in pan until hot, mixing well.

title: chewy breadsticks
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, sprinkle yeast over warm water; stir to dissolve.
At medium speed, beat in honey, then gradually beat in 3 cups flour; beat well.
With heavy-duty mixer or wooden spoon, gradually add enough of the remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes, adding more flour as necessary.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: stuffed cabbages
directions: Mix meat well with eggs, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Roll in cabbage leaf and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Heat all ingredients except cheese and pimento in double boiler.
Add diced cheese, stirring until melted.
Add pimento. Refrigerate.
Can be used as dip or spread.

title: virginia turner's brownies(memory to cheryl carson's mom)
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat; add sugar and cocoa and stir.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add flour and stir.
Add vanilla and eggs and stir again.
Pour in greased and floured pan, approximately 8 x 10-inch, and cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
When done, take from oven and turn upside down immediately on paper sack.
Use icing recipe.

title: honey date bread
directions: Mix dates, shortening, brown sugar, honey, vanilla, mandarin peel, hot water and mandarin juice.
Stir until well mixed, let stand 10 minutes.
Add egg.
Resift flour with soda and salt into date mixture.
Stir to a thick batter.
Add nuts, mix.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack and cool before slicing or storing.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: spaghetti corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger and sausage together with minced onion, then drain.
Cook spaghetti separately and drain. Add corn, mushroom pieces, cream of mushroom soup, salt and pepper and garlic powder to hamburger mixture and cook about 2 minutes until soup is mixed well.
Add spaghetti, sour cream and cheese to mixture and stir together.
Pour mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and sprinkle seasoned crumbs on top.
If casserole seems dry, add a little milk.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls size of walnut.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Mash each ball flat (approximately 2-inches round).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tennessee stack cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add molasses.
Beat until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla to creamed mixture.

title: cast and fire's margaritas
directions: In
a
container,
empty
frozen
limeade.
Add
can of water. Add
the
frozen orange juice, tequila and Triple Sec; mix
well. Then
you
can
add
ice cubes or crushed ice; mix until chilled.
Rub
a
piece
of lime around the rim of your glass
or cup and dip the edge into the coarse salt.
Pour the Margarita mixture
into the glasses, with or without the ice. A
blender
is also excellent to use.
Add enough crushed ice and blend until you have a slush.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce (about 6 cups) in bottom of salad bowl.
Add celery in a layer, then green peppers, next add onions in a layer. Finish with drained peas.
Carefully put mayonnaise over the top. Sprinkle on sugar.
Layer cheese over this.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Add bacon bits on top and serve.

title: beau monde vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: chicken with walnut filling
directions: Use a blender to chop chicken and walnuts.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Fill rolls or bread.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups of filling. Yummy!

title: deviled tofu
directions: Mash tofu; add everything except tofu.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate, then spread cocktail sauce on top of the cream cheese.
Top with crabmeat and cheese.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Take greased Bundt pan.
Take pieces and roll in cinnamon mixture.
Place into pan and as you layer, sprinkle with pecans.
After all biscuits are in pan melt margarine and pour over this.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit lightly and refrigerate until set.
Additional fruits can be added to this such as strawberries or a can of fruit cocktail, drained.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Thinly slice cucumbers and onions.
Stir salt into cucumbers and onions; let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in a large pan; bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers and onions, but don't boil, just heat thoroughly.
Put into clean sterilized jars.
Cool and store.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef, then add the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
It can be prepared in a large electric frypan.

title: todd's cookies
directions: In a small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips, Rice Krispies and raisins. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes a whole lot.

title: fay's broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Cook until done, not brown.
Cook broccoli in microwave as directed on package.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add onion and oleo; mix well.
Add cornbread mix and mix well.
Drain broccoli and add to mixture, then add cheese and mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Let cherries mixed with sugar stand for 1 hour.
Add pineapple and refrigerate.
Just before serving, add 3 bananas, sliced.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a bowl.
In a medium size saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and pepper. Bring this to a boil.
Let cool completely.
Pour over the vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix together.
Chill.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vinegar and water, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown chops.
Prepare stuffing according to box directions. In oblong baking dish, layer apple filling, chops (salt and pepper to taste) and stuffing.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
I serve with mashed potatoes and use apple filling as gravy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice in 2 cups of water.
When dry, add hot milk.
Beat sugar with eggs.
When almost dry, add egg mixture and stir until done.
Put in dishes or platter and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: easy sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: delicious pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in shells.
Leave in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours. Serve.

title: black bean dip
directions: Combine all in processor.
Chop coarsely.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Place package of cream cheese on serving platter.
Place drained crabmeat over cream cheese and pour chili sauce over crabmeat.
Serve with your choice of cracker.

title: joey's favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients together.
Sift the flour, cinnamon and salt together.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture; add baking soda and milk.
Stir raisins and oats into dough.
Drop very small amount from a teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes until cookies are set, but not brown.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, salt and milk together in a saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat until slightly thick.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Add 1/2 cup nuts, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until done. Drain, peel and mash the potatoes.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place mixture in the casserole and sprinkle with the remaining sugar. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: yummy barbecue ribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with salt and pepper.
Place ribs in broiler pan under broiler for 10 minutes on each side and remove excess fat. Put onions in crock-pot.
Slice ribs into serving pieces and put in crock-pot.
Pour barbecue sauce over ribs.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 4 to 6 hours.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until hot; stir constantly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill at least one hour.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons.
Microwave beans as directed on package; drain well.
Add mushrooms and onions to reserved 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Cook and stir on medium-high heat 10 minutes; drain.
Add bacon, hot cooked.

title: old fashion egg pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well and add milk.
Mix sugar and flour and add to first mixture.
Beat egg whites (not stiff) and fold in. Sprinkle with nutmeg and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/8-inch thick.
Parboil 5 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain in colander.
Stir onions in cream of chicken soup, cheese, salt and pepper.

title: holiday pecans
directions: Put pecans on tray.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Salt pecans when they come out of the oven and are still hot.
Serve warm.

title: steamed whole fish with scallions and ginger
directions: Have the fish cleaned and scaled but leve the head on (if any cutting has to be done, trim the tail).
Slash the fish to the center bone at 1 1/2 inch intervals.
Place the fish on a platter; sprinkle with the sherry and let stand 20 minutes.
Trim and wash the scallions, slit in half lengthwise and cut into 2 inch pieces. Shred the ginger slices into matchstick pieces.
Sprinkle the soy sauce and sesame oil atop the fish, then crisscross the ginger shreds on top of the fish and place the scallion pieces atop the ginger.
Place the steaming rack inside the steaming wok.
Add 5 to 6 cups of water to the wok and bring to the boil.
Lower the platter onto the rack, cover the wok and steam the fish over high heat for 12 to 15 minutes, depending on size and girth.
The fish is done when the flesh pulls away from the bone easily.
Remove the platter from the wok with a plate lifter or pot holders.
Place the fish platter on a larger platter and bring to the table.
Enjoy!

title: rabbit surprise
directions: Brown rabbit in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly until tender, about 1 hour.
Serves 2.

title: healthy fried chicken(southern fried chicken)
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Coat a shallow metal pan with non-stick spray, set aside.
Pour buttermilk into a shallow bowl. Add chicken, turning to coat.
Refrigerate chicken in buttermilk for at least 15 minutes, turning occasionally.
On a plate, combine corn flakes, paprika, salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper.
One at a time, dip each side of chicken into the corn flake mixture, pressing firmly to coat.
Stir the mixture occasionally with a fork to keep seasoning evenly
mixed.
Place chicken on the prepared pan.
Coat the chicken with non-stick spray, turning once.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown and the juices run clear when chicken is pricked.

title: chocolate nut cups(makes about 4 dozen cups)
directions: Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and vegetable oil in top of double boiler.
Place over hot water, stirring until chips are completely melted and well blended.
Remove from heat; stir in peanuts.
Cool slightly; drop by teaspoonfuls into decorative nut cups.
Garnish with additional peanuts, peanut butter chips or sprinkle with finely chopped peanuts.
Chill until firm.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt margarine and
cocoa in pan. Remove from heat; add buttermilk, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cake while hot.
You can add nuts to icing or sprinkle on top.
Great for a crowd.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and peanuts in electric frying pan. Cook at 350° for 10 minutes or until syrup is golden tan.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour into buttered baking sheet and spread thinly. Cool.
Break into serving pieces.

title: hot yeast rolls
directions: Combine
sugar and salt with 2 cups lukewarm water in a large mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in the same mixture.
Stir in
egg. Add
shortening.
Add half the flour, stirring well. Add remaining
flour
gradually,
stirring until dough leaves sides of the bowl.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease the surface.
Cover with a damp towel and place in the refrigerator
for 1 hour.
Punch the dough down and shape into rolls.
Place
on
a baking sheet and let rise in a warm place for 2
hours.
Bake
at
for
12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 3 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Remove wrappers from Kisses. In a large bowl, beat shortening and peanut butter until well blended. Add 1/3 cup granulated sugar and brown sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to peanut butter mixture. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Immediately place Kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so cookie cracks around edges. Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Cool completely. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal and salt.
Add soda to buttermilk and combine with cornmeal.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Heat bacon grease in 9-inch iron skillet or 8-inch square pan.
Pour half of batter into pan, sprinkle half of cheese over it, then pour in rest of batter.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at about 400° for about 35 minutes.

title: old-fashioned sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 214°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and sour cream.
Mix flour and soda together and add gradually to butter mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy (about 2 minutes).
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes (mixture will not fit in a Bundt pan).

title: carol's pasta fagoli(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a large Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion; cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add garlic; cook for 1 minute longer. Add tomatoes, oregano, hot pepper flakes and broth.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Add beans and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: honey orange prune bread
directions: Cream together
butter
and
honey.
Add egg and orange peel. Beat well.
Sift
flour,
baking powder, soda and salt; add to honey
mixture alternately with orange juice.
Add nuts and prunes.
Turn
into a greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches). Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned dressing
directions: Beat egg; add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Boil and stir until thick.
Add butter and chopped onion.
Thin as desired with milk.

title: lentils with rice
directions: Combine lentils, water, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until lentils are partially cooked, about 5 to 7 minutes. Add rice and cumin.
Cook until water is absorbed.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Place chicken in a large skillet with the water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 18 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.

title: grilled turkey tenders
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinade overnight. Preheat grill; drain the Turkey and discard the marinade. Grill Tenders on medium heat for 6 - 8 minutes per side, or until no longer pink in center.

title: cookie cake
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, cream sugar, vanilla and butter.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well.
Gradually add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour mixture in pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: chocolate syrup pound cake
