directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add chocolate syrup and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and continue to beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Start in cold oven.
Do not open the door for 1 hour.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serve hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir ingredients until blended.
Cover; chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Top with 1/4 cup chopped toasted walnuts.
Makes 2 2/3 cups.
Serve with King's Hawaiian bread.
Hollow center of bread and use as a bowl.
Dip extra pieces.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup of sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Add the milk and water, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup of sugar and gradually pour hot mixture over them while stirring.
Return to double boiler and cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Add lemon juice; mix well.
Cool and pour into pie shell and top with meringue made by beating the 3 egg whites until quite stiff, gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar while continuing to beat until stiff.
Bake in 300° oven until light brown.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, pudding mix and pumpkin pie spice in small mixer bowl.
Blend with electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Top with remaining whipped topping.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice bags in water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add chicken and soup and stir.
Add milk to desired consistency.
Heat and serve.
Salt to add zest!!!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make jello according to directions on box.
Place in refrigerator.
Wash cranberries.
In saucepan, add 2 cups cold water to cranberries.
Boil rapidly until skin pops open (about 5 minutes).
Press through sieve to remove skins and seeds.
Add sugar; boil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool.
Mix well.
When jello begins to congeal, fold in cranberry-orange mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: 11:00 casserole
directions: Cook and chop bacon; cook and drain spinach well.
Cool.
Thaw Welsh Rarebit; place 1/3 of Rarebit in pan (8 x 8-inch).
Add spinach, bacon and drained chestnuts.
Top with remaining Rarebit. Sprinkle with onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: spaghetti with italian seafood sauce
directions: In large pot, cook onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Add pasta sauce and zucchini.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover and simmer 8 minutes or until tender.
Serve over hot spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef and minced onion in skillet.
Transfer to 2-quart casserole, discarding any fat.
Add parsley and Worcestershire sauce.

title: sinfully chocolate
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add pudding in cake mix.
In pan, after spraying, pour coconut and spread out, then put pecans over coconut.
Pour cake batter over this.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Punch holes in top of cake with fork.
Cover with Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut.
Let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and flour together in saucepan.
Mix egg yolks and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Pour in other mixture and cook until thick.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with meringue.

title: 1-2-3 salsa
directions: Combine ketchup, taco sauce and green chilies in a bowl. Depending on your taste, you may choose mild, medium or hot taco sauce.
Use either tortilla chips or corn chips for dipping. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cocoa pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in dry ingredients, alternately with coffee and buttermilk.
Pour into greased angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cheesy chili casserole
directions: Brown beef and green pepper; drain.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Add 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz.
Stir until melted.
Spread 1 cup meat mixture into bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with 1 cup chips.
Repeat layering twice, topping with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining chips, tomatoes and process cheese spread. Continue baking for 5 minutes, or until cheese spread is melted.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix butter, oatmeal, soda, flour, brown sugar and salt and put 3/4 of mixture into jelly roll pan.
Melt caramels, butter and milk; pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove and place chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Top with remaining crumb mix.
Bake another 15 minutes at 350°.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Bring to a boil and mix with mixture:
margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola. Cool this for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups miniature marshmallows and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured pans for 30 minutes.
(Batter is very thin.)

title: scotcheroos
directions: In a large pan, cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt over hot water the chips, stirring constantly.
Spread over mixture.

title: 14 carat cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, salad oil and eggs.
Mix well. Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut. Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a
13 x 9-inch layer pan that is greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes. Remove from oven and cool. Fill layers and frost top and sides with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken caper
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown chicken in butter in a skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 40 minutes.
Add garlic, olives, capers, liquid, water and parsley.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with buttered and parslied new potatoes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice and soda in pitcher; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Pour into punch bowl.
Yield: 72 servings.

title: chili(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Simmer 20 more minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes just before using to prevent discoloration. Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat on low speed until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls into a hot greased griddle.
Fry over medium heat until crisp and brown on underside.
Turn and brown other side.
Serves as vegetables or main dish.

title: easy broccoli bake
directions: In shallow casserole, combine soup, milk, and soy sauce.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir.
Top with remaining onions, bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: dirty rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add rice, mushrooms and bouillon soup with enough water to make 2 cups.
Bake, covered, until moisture is absorbed.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: custard coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour until fluffy.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2-inch pie pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop onions and celery.
With 1 tablespoon butter, saute until tender.
Bring 1 cup water to boil; add 1 cup rice.
Let set while preparing cheese.
Melt cheese, mushroom soup and 1/2 can water until cheese melts.
Put unthawed broccoli in casserole dish.
Pour onions and rice into cheese.
Stir.
Pour over broccoli; stir and bake 30 minutes or until hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all and beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Shape into balls and fry until brown; drain.
Heat and serve in sauce.

title: cherry cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix and bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.
Then use 1 can of cherry pie filling to fill top of cupcakes.
Serve.

title: fried cabbage and noodles
directions: Saute chopped onion in bacon drippings until golden brown. Shred cabbage and add to mixture.
Cook until tender.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
After they are blanched and drained, combine with cabbage mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the flour and sugar.
Bring the oleo, cocoa, water and Crisco to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients. Add the buttermilk, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese soup(serves 8)
directions: Boil celery and green onion in 2 cups water for 5 minutes. Saute white onion in margarine, add flour and blend well.
Boil milk and broth.
Stir into white onion mixture with wire whisk. Add cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in prepared mustard and boiled vegetables including water in which they were cooked. Heat and serve.
Freezes well.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together, chill, then roll in rest of nuts.

title: apple goodie
directions: Place apples in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with sugar and cinnamon.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl, mixing well. Spread evenly over apples.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: no-fool cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk in bowl; mix well.
Spread in prepared dish.
Spoon blackberries onto batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and center springs back when touched.
May substitute favorite canned or fresh fruit for blackberries. Yield:
8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend sweet potatoes and ingredients with mixer and pour in baking dish.

title: miss edith's monster cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together oleo and peanut butter until combined in a large bowl. Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by large spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and other dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: tuna bumstead
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put large tablespoon of mix on hamburger bun.
Wrap in foil and put in preheated oven (250°) for 30 minutes.

title: rock candy
directions: Cook all ingredients without stirring to 250°.
Pour quickly into greased square pan.
Chill until firm.
Turn out of pan and crack into pieces.
Add flavored extracts and food coloring, if desired.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, salt and egg yolks.
Add pineapple. Cook on the stove until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and put on top.
Brown in oven.

title: coconut pie
directions: This pie makes its own crust.
To well beaten eggs, add sugar, vanilla, coconut, salt, milk, butter, flour sifted with cream of tartar and sugar; beat well.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook 1 pound (3 cups)
macaroni by directions on package; drain and rinse with cold water (makes 6 to 8 cups of cooked macaroni).
May refrigerate until cool.

title: hot chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, celery, nuts, onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Toast bread on one side; butter other side and spread with chicken mixture.
Top with potato chips.
Heat on baking sheet in oven (425°) for 12 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4.

title: helen's 12 bean soup
directions: Wash beans; put in large kettle.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Next morning, drain and add 2 quarts water.
Simmer slowly while covered for 3 to 4 hours.
Now add 1 large onion (chopped), 1 quart canned tomatoes and 1 teaspoon chili powder to taste.
Simmer an additional 40 to 60 minutes.
Pieces of lean ham or a ham bone may be added at first cooking, if desired. Vegetable water flavors as well.
Carrots, celery and other seasonings may be added.
Use your imagination.
Freezes well. Delicious and nutritious!

title: vegetable pizza
directions: You may use any of the vegetables listed (chop into small pieces):
broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery, green peppers, onions, red cabbage, mushrooms.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In bowl blend together soup, milk, mayo and mustard.
Stir in cheese, tuna and pimiento.
Gently fold in cooked macaroni.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs, melted butter and paprika; sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through, 45 to 50 minutes.
Garnish casserole with parsley sprig, if desired.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: baked lentils with cheese
directions: In a shallow baking dish (about 9 x 3-inches), mix the lentils, water, bay leaf, salt, pepper, marjoram, sage, thyme, onions, garlic and tomatoes.
Then cover tightly with foil and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover; stir in carrots and celery.
Bake, covered, for 40 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in green pepper and parsley.
Sprinkle cheese on top; bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.
This is an excellent meatless dish; high in protein and very tasty.

title: mexican cheese with green chiles
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Place in an 8-inch square baking dish
or quiche pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let sit
for
minutes,
then cut into squares. Serve hot.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Blend Ricotta and cream cheese well.
Blend in sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and butter.
Fold in sour cream and blend well.
Pour into 10-inch buttered spring pan.
Place in cold oven and turn heat to 325° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door.
Turn off oven and leave for 2 to 3 hours.
Cool and put fruit on top (cherries, pineapple, strawberries).

title: cinnamon lollipops
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a saucepan.
Place over medium heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to hard crack stage without stirring.
Wipe crystals from sides of pan frequently with a fork wrapped in a damp cloth, or place lid on pan and let steam dissolve the crystals.
(Be careful that candy does not boil over.)
Remove from heat.
Add coloring and flavoring.
Stir only to mix.
Drop by teaspoon on well-buttered flat surface.
Insert skewers, or pour candy on wooden sticks.
Makes 6 to 9 lollipops. Wrap in waxed paper.

title: janell's beans
directions: Cut ham into small pieces.
Add all ingredients to the beans, adding just enough water to cover beans.
Cook slowly until done (5 to 6 hours).

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in cake mix, cherry pie filling and oil; blend well.
Spread in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
(Surface of cake will be bumpy.)
Cool completely.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: In a blender, mix together the egg, milk, oil, peanut butter and banana.
In a separate bowl, mix together the flour and baking powder.
Pour the contents of the blender into the bowl with the flour; stir only until mixed.
Cook pancakes, turning only once. Serve with choice of toppings:
pourable fruit, applesauce, honey, yogurt, cream cheese, syrup.

title: bean salad *
directions: Combine all beans in large bowl.
Add pepper and onion.
In a jar, mix remaining ingredients; shake well to combine and pour over vegetables.
Toss to combine.

title: cocoa fudge pie
directions: Mix all together, then pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Add powder sugar, cocoa, milk & vanilla in bowl. DO NOT STIR. Put stick of butter in center of bowl. Microwave for 2 1/2 min. remove and beat well with electric mixer. Add peanut butter put into pan and refrigerate.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut
biscuits in half.
Wrap dough around cheese cubes. Drop in hot oil and fry until brown.
Drain.

title: stir-fry beef
directions: Cut steak into thin strips (wafer thin steak works well). Pour soy sauce, Italian dressing and sugar over steak.
Toss to coat meat well.
Let set for at least 15 minutes; can be refrigerated for longer.
Heat skillet until hot.
Pour meat and marinade into hot skillet and stir until meat is tender and marinade reduces.
This is good over rice or by itself.

title: peanut butter crunch bars
directions: Melt butter over low heat in saucepan. In a mixing bowl, blend peanut butter and sugar. Add the melted butter and continue to blend. Stir in cereal and spread evenly onto a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a separate saucepan, melt the chocolate chips over low heat. Spread melted chocolate evenly over bars. Refrigerate to cool. Cut into bars. Makes approximately 30 bars.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine in large bowl, pudding mix and milk, blend well.
Add in Cool Whip (save some to use as topping) and sour cream.
Layer in a large dish- vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Repeat layers and top with Cool Whip and more wafers.

title: great salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil.
Slowly add the oils and mix continuously for 10 minutes.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: hearty potato-ham soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add potatoes, green pepper and green onion.
Cook until slightly tender.
Add 2 cups water, salt, paprika and pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Melt butter and pour into pie pan.
Add onion and cheese to coat bottom of pan.
Add biscuits on top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes (do not burn cheese).
Turn onto plate.
Serve warm.

title: almond bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add cooled margarine.
Add salt and flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix in almond flavoring.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with a little powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until light brown.

title: holiday candy
directions: Melt chocolate using double boiler method (water in saucepan and another pan on top to put chocolate in).
When melted, stir into nuts and pretzels.
When totally covered, put on wax paper to dry and harden.
When hard, break up and store in airtight container.
Enjoy!

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour; mix 1 cup buttermilk and 1 teaspoon soda (let it work).
Alternate flour and milk to other ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites, nuts, coconut and vanilla.

title: make-ahead potatoes(serves 12)
directions: Place potatoes in Dutch oven or large kettle; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain and place in a bowl.
Mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, 4 tablespoons butter, onion and salt.
Stir until smooth and the cream cheese and butter have melted.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt remaining butter; drizzle over potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate or bake immediately, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes; uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; cool.
Peel and dice eggs.
Add all other ingredients; mix everything together gently.
Store in airtight container and chill.
Best if let set overnight.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Boil water, bouillon cubes, onion and celery for 10 minutes. Add potatoes and vegetables and boil for 20 minutes.
Whisk the soup and milk until smooth.
Add soup and cheese to vegetable mixture; stir until cheese is melted.
This soup freezes well!

title: shrimp orlean
directions: Melt butter, add onion, celery and garlic; cook until tender. Combine soup and sour cream, add ketchup and onion mixture.
Cook until it bubbles.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Serve over rice.

title: chili
directions: Fry onions until brown, then add hamburger.
Fry until brown, then add tomatoes.
Put this in large kettle where 1 package of spaghetti has been cooked, then add beans and chili powder.

title: nena's chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix chocolate milk, condensed cream and sugar.
Fold in Cool whip.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Add sour cream, half of the cheese and half of the fried onions.
Stir in the soup; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Return to oven until cheese is melted and brown.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 260° or until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
In a heavy mixing bowl (not plastic), beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Continue beating while pouring in the hot syrup in a thin stream.
Add vanilla and nuts. Continue beating until mixture holds its shape.
Drop on waxed paper from the tip of a buttered spoon.
This makes about 4 dozen candies.

title: quick and easy banana pudding
directions: Put a layer of vanilla wafers in bowl, then a layer of sliced banana until you use all wafers and bananas.
Mix instant pudding and pour over bananas and wafers.
You can eat it cold or warm in microwave for 4 minutes.
Good either way.

title: oven-fried zucchini spears
directions: Mix breadcrumbs, cheese, garlic powder, paprika and pepper in a shallow dish.
Set aside.
Cut zucchini lengthwise in 4 pieces; cut each piece in half crosswise.
Put zucchini in plastic bag. Add oil and water and shake.
Dredge zucchini in breadcrumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 475° until brown and tender, about 10 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: crabmeat melt
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions and seasonings.
Blend well.
Gently fold in crab and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, spread crab mixture on muffins; top with tomato slices and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugar-free teething crackers for baby
directions: Stir flour and cereal in a bowl.
Add oil or margarine and blend well.
Add enough water to make like a pie dough.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into cracker or cookie shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes in a preheated 350° oven until crisp and golden.

title: mandarin orange torte
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add sherbet; fold in whipped cream and oranges.
Break cake in pieces and place in 7 x 11-inch pan. Pour orange mix over.
Chill several hours.
Serve with whipped cream and mandarin oranges.

title: souper eggplant casserole
directions: Cube unpeeled eggplant and saute in skillet in butter and oil with onion and garlic 15 minutes or until tender.
Combine soup and milk and add to eggplant, salt and pepper in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix or croutons and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly and golden.

title: bacon-wrapped corn
directions: Pull husks away from corn.
Wrap corn with a bacon strip.
Pat with butter or oleo.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Re-wrap corn in husks.
Place in foil wraps.
Sprinkle on 2 tablespoons water. Wrap and seal.
Cook on grill 30 to 40 minutes, turning once.

title: shrimp fra diavob
directions: Mix the dry spices together and sprinkle on the shrimp. Lightly coat shrimp with flour.
Saute coated shrimp and minced garlic in a frying pan using olive oil.
After 2 minutes, add wine and continue to cook over medium heat, reducing liquid by one half.
Add clam juice, then fold in the marinara sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Serve over hot pasta.
Serves 4.

title: mexican nacho dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese with dry taco mix.
Spread on the bottom of large serving platter.
Then spread 2 or 3 tablespoons of Mexican salsa on top.
Layer chopped onion, shredded lettuce, chopped tomato and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top with sliced black olives.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix well.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.

title: caramel nut bars(serves 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Beat cake mix, cereal and butter in large bowl until dough forms. Reserve 1 cup of dough for topping. Press remaining dough evenly onto bottom of prepared pan.

title: roasted pepper dip
directions: Stir soup with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Then stir in peppers.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bacon in a small skillet.
Add and lightly brown minced onion.
Combine in a 2 1/2-quart casserole, the beans, bacon and onion.
Mix tomato based barbecue sauce, corn syrup, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard; add to beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: super sesame chicken
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
In frying pan, combine sesame seed and oil; cook until golden.
Cool.
Stir in soy sauce, sugar, ginger, pepper, garlic and 1/2 the green onions.
Mix in chicken. Cover and chill 1 to 4 hours (I have chilled overnight).
Pour meat and marinade onto cookie sheet in a single layer.
Broil until golden; stir often.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Stir in one ingredient at a time to avoid lumping.
Mix by hand.
Put into a greased Bundt pan or two bread pans, three if the small size.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Keep loosely covered at room temperature.

title: spam salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain; do not chill. Return to pan; drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add grated cheese, salt, pepper and onion; mix well until cheese melts.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Great the next day.

title: asparagus with raspberry vinaigrette dressing
directions: Steam a good sized bunch of fresh asparagus spears until tender-crisp, then cool quickly in cold water to retain color. Arrange a bed of red leaf lettuce on a platter and arrange asparagus over the lettuce.
Keep chilled in the refrigerator.

title: party chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts, flat in greased oven pan or Pyrex dish. Salt and pepper.
Top each breast with cheese.
Add mushrooms. Mix soup and wine.
Pour over breasts.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Dribble melted butter.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Sprinkle parsley on top before serving.
Serves 8.

title: fourth of july beans
directions: Brown hamburger separately.
Fry bacon separately.
Mix together onion, brown sugar, catsup, mustard, vinegar and salt. Add to the mixture the hamburger, bacon and beans (drained).
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° or use crock-pot equivalent.
Stir occasionally.
Will freeze.

title: cranberry sour cream salad(serves 10)
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Cool. Fold in sour cream or yogurt and pecans.
Pour in mold; chill until firm.

title: my momma's fruit salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl dump all ingredients; mix well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Five minutes before dish goes on table, top with 2 bananas.

title: crab-cream cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, onions and dill weed.
Unroll crescents onto greased baking sheet.
Do not separate dough.
Press dough into rectangle.
Spoon crabmeat lengthwise along center of dough.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over crabmeat.
Fold long edges of dough over cheese mixture, slightly overlapping edges.
Pinch edges together to seal.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Lightly brush dough with egg yolk.
Cut slits in top of dough.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch slices and serve warm.

title: three bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a 5-quart crock-pot.
Fill to top with water.
Cook on high approximately 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Combine oats, flour, baking soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips; mix well.
Chill dough for 1 hour, or until firm.
Roll dough into 1 1/2-inch balls; place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: onion rings
directions: Cut onion rings 1/8-inch thick. Soak in ice water, sweetened with 2 or 3 teaspoons sugar. Dip in batter.
Mix flour, oil, salt and water. Beat egg white until stiff.
Fold in other ingredients.

title: very easy lasagna
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: easy sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour, sugar, oil, sour cream and eggs; beat on low for 1 minute. Beat on high 4 minutes. Add pecans, if desired. Put in greased and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven; set to 325° and bake 50 minutes.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Dilute mushroom soup in kettle, adding green chilies and sour cream.
Heat soup mixture on low while grating cheese and slicing olives.
In 9 x 13-inch dish, spoon in just enough soup mixture to cover the bottom.
Then layer as follows:
corn tortillas, soup mixture, cheese and olives.
Continue layering and end with a layer of the soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt.
Slowly add sugar.
Beat to stiff peaks.
Add chips or nuts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies on greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven.
Turn off oven and leave cookies in overnight.

title: baked steak
directions: Bake at 325° in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place steak in bottom of pan.
Mix soup and rest of ingredients together and pour over steak.
Bake covered for 1 hour.
Stir and rotate meat in pan. Cook 30 minutes more or until meat is tender.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: penuche icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring. Stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Cool to lukewarm. Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: taco chicken
directions: Mix all liquids together and layer chips, chicken, cheese and liquid mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, sugar and peaches up until well blended.
Put butter in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and melt.
Pour mixture in butter and bake until brown.

title: poached red snapper
directions: Stir wine, lime and jalapeno in a 12-inch skillet.
Add red snapper.
Add enough water to cover fillets.
Heat to a simmer over low heat.
Cook fillets 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Remove from liquid and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl beat oil and sugars; add eggs and beat until well blended.
In a separate bowl sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and spices.
Stir into egg mixture, then add carrots, currants and walnuts; beat well.
Finally add the vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour batter into two greased and floured baking pans or one 8 x 12-inch greased and floured rectangular pan.
Bake for about one hour at 350°.
If making cupcakes, fill cups only half-full and bake for only 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.

title: apple cranberry pie(for 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine sugars, flour and cinnamon.
Add fruit.
Mix well.
Turn into pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover and cut slits into top crust.
Seal edges. Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese glazed chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour, paprika and salt.
Brown in oil and butter; add sherry.
Cook, covered, until tender; then add Chablis and lemon juice.
Blend cream and cornstarch and add to juice in pan, stirring until thickened.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover pan until cheese melts.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture clings.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: In bowl, combine pineapple, cranberries, oranges and pecans. Fold in whipped topping.
Serve in a pretty crystal bowl.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Add vegetables and cook for a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes on a low heat.

title: good kraut
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch strips; add other ingredients and put in shallow 7 x 11-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: portuguese potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; cube and put in large casserole dish.
Cube cheese and sprinkle over potatoes, then sprinkle onion, pimento, parsley, paprika and Nature's Seasons salt.
Cube bread slices and arrange on top.
Melt butter and pour over casserole.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: low cholesterol pound cake
directions: Cream margarine in large bowl.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg substitute, 1/4 cup at a time. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning with and ending with the flour mixture.
Stir in flavoring.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil without stirring.
Keep saucepan covered
first three minutes to prevent crystals from forming on sides
of
pan.	While syrup is cooking, beat until stiff enough to hold a point
the egg whites with the cream of tartar.
Pour hot syrup very
slowly
in
a
thin
stream into stiffly beaten egg whites.	Beat
until
syrup
and whites are well
blended and stiff.
Add
vanilla.
Beat
until
frosting holds its shape.
Spread
over cake.
Sprinkle with candies of colored sugar.
May add a drop
or	2 of food coloring to tint frosting.

title: pea salad 2
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Bake chicken; tear into small pieces.
In pot over medium heat, mix 1 can of tomatoes and 2 cans of chicken soup.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer chicken pieces, tortillas, tomato-soup mixture and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbles.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits, roll in dry mixture.
Boil liquid for 2 minutes, layer 1/2 biscuits in Bundt or tube pan.
Pour 1/2 liquid over top.
Layer with other 1/2 biscuits and top with rest of liquid.
Bake at 350 for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: little smokies in picante sauce
directions: Place smokies and picante sauce in crock-pot and cook on high for 1 hour and stir occasionally.

title: orange nut balls
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, powdered sugar, margarine and pecans. Add orange juice; mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar, nuts or coconut.
Freeze until needed.
Delicious!

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into 2-inch cubes and brown in salad oil in skillet. Place in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil; pour over beef.
Cover, and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: m&m cookies in a jar
directions: Put lid on jar tightly and add gift tag with ribbon.

title: venison - hunter's style(very good!)
directions: Cut the venison into 2-inch squares.
Salt and pepper well. Brown venison in butter, slowly.
Add the onions and brown lightly. Add the ham, minced fine.
Add garlic, thyme and bay leaves, chopped fine.
Let them all brown a few minutes, then add the flour and brown.
Add the wine and simmer 5 minutes.
Add a quart of water and cover.
Cook 1 hour over low-medium heat.
Add lemon juice.
Cook this in a heavy pan until tender.
Serve on a heated platter with the gravy poured over the meat.

title: pannekoeken(crepes)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients to make a fairly thin batter.
Use a dipper or ladle to put 1/2 cupful on a hot griddle using a circular motion.
The Pannekoeken should be quite thin.
It may be turned once for a short cooking period on the flip side.
Griddle should be at medium heat.
Makes about 2 dozen (8-inch) crepes.
Serve with banana sauce.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Mix ketchup and brown sugar and heat on stove.
Wrap bacon around chestnuts and bake until bacon is crisp.
Put toothpicks through them to hold together.
Dip chestnuts and bacon roll in brown sugar and ketchup before eating.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer pie filling, then pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix across pan.
Cut up 2 sticks butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brunch rolls
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Put cheese mixture on top of 1 package of rolled out rolls in pan.
Layer 2nd package on top of cheese; fork whip egg white; brush on top.
Bake until puffy and lightly brown on top.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Blend well.
Can be served at once or kept in the refrigerator for several days.
Also freezes well.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain. Mix taco seasoning to taste. Cut chilies in half lengthwise. Spray bottom and sides of baking dish (butter). Cover bottom of pan with chilies. Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over the chilies. Top with meat mix. Layer remaining chilies over meat. Sprinkle remaining cheese over chilies. Combine milk, beaten eggs, salt, pepper and flour. Pour over meat and chilies. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until mixture is set. Let cool for 5 minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips in large bowl.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: picante con questo dip
directions: Cut cheese into small cubes and combine with milk and picante sauce in a saucepan. Heat until sauce is smooth. Serve with chips or vegetable dippers. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cut peppers, onions and squash into small cubes.
Bring turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed, cloves, vinegar, salt and sugar to a boil.
Pour over peppers, onions and squash.
Let stand 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Heat and bring to a boil.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Continue to simmer while packing in hot and sterilized jars.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, salt and soda.
Add buttermilk, oil, eggs and corn.
Beat and mix well.
Stir in jalapenos and onion. Grease 9 x 14-inch baking dish or large iron skillet with 2 teaspoons cooking oil and heat well.
Pour half of batter. Sprinkle with half of cheese and repeat.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Cook on low heat, onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add onion and celery to the crumbs and seasonings.
Stir in beaten eggs and enough broth or hot water to make a moist mixture, about the consistency of cornbread batter.
Pour into greased pan and bake about 30 minutes or until browned.
Don't overcook.
Dressing should be moist.
Cut into squares.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: walnut kolache (roll)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk.
Add oleo, sugar and salt and mix well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add egg and dissolved yeast. Stir in 1/2 of flour and beat well until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts, then gradually mix in remaining flour.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto an oiled baking sheet.
Brush with butter.
Let rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Use a teaspoon to press out a center in the dough which can be filled with jams or apricots or prunes dipped in 1/4 cup ground nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Combine powdered sugar, hot water and vanilla and stir until smooth.
Spread on kolache while it is still warm from oven.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: homemade almond joys
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Chill about 1 hour, then roll into balls.
Place on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in saucepan.
Dip candy balls into chocolate mixture and replace on wax paper to cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Beat in egg, then peanut butter.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt along with the oats.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pans at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter honey delites
directions: Mix the peanut butter, honey and dry milk until mixture is smooth.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread in an 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 48 squares and place a peanut half on each, if desired.
(Remember each piece has 60 calories.) Makes 48 pieces.

title: maine clam or fish chowder
directions: Saute diced salt pork until crisp; cut up and add onions.
Cut up and add potatoes; add water to cover.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add fish or clams.
Add rich milk or half and half.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Grease and flour one large angel food cake pan.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour and soda.
Add vanilla, lemon or almond and sour cream; mix well.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy and economical lasagna
directions: First layer:
Lay down 3 lasagna noodles.

title: soft mints
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended (by hand).
If using different colors, divide dough to color separately.
Knead color into dough until color is even.
Take small balls and roll until approximately 1/2-inch diameter.
Cut into small pieces.
Dry several hours on cookie sheets.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water and add gelatine and strawberry jello; mix until dissolved.
Mix remaining ingredients together (except sour cream).
Pour 1/2 remaining ingredients in with gelatine and jello mixture.
Put sour cream on top, then add rest of ingredients. Chill until set.

title: beef roast
directions: Place on high in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Cover half with water.
After 3 to 4 hours, add gravy.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Add lard to salt and flour.
Put egg and vinegar in a bowl and work flour, salt and lard mixture together.
Bake crusts at 375°.

title: recipe of heaven
directions: Spread Faith generously around each lovely day God has given you.
Add Hope to every good deed and thank God for His graces. Take Charity and sift all around to your friends, neighbors or anyone near.
Bake for a lifetime and use it with Love.
It's satisfying to the heart.

title: mrs. f.l.b. flood's cinnamon buns
directions: Scald milk; add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure into bowl 2/3 cup lukewarm water and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Crumble and stir in yeast.
Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Add and stir in eggs and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add and stir in an additional 3 cups flour.
Mix until dough forms a ball.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead dough quickly and lightly until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and set in warm place free from draft.
Let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bar
directions: Mix sugar, butter and vanilla together.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour and chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: spanish rice and shrimp
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in oil in nonstick pan for 3 minutes; add rice, chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper and cook for 1 minute.
Add enough water to chicken broth to make 2 1/2 cups and add to rice.
Puree tomato; stir into skillet and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Stir in vinegar, red pepper seasoning and shrimp.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (in order listed).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Recipe may be cut in half.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Remove 1 cup cake mix (set aside).
Beat first three ingredients with fork until cake is absorbed.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: tart shells
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Pinch dough and press in small muffin pans.
Cook at 400° about 8 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a two-quart casserole, stir together the soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Add the macaroni and onions.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle the top with the cheese; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Return to the oven for another 5 or 10 minutes, or until the cheese melts.
Serves four.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Add juice of cherries, pineapple and lemon juice to jello mixture.
Cool until it starts to gel.
Add cherries, pineapple, marshmallows, pecans (optional) and Cool Whip.
Mold in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into a large skillet and brown evenly; drain.
Stir eggs, corn meal, cream-style corn, milk and vegetables together.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet or 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Top evenly with browned ground beef followed by the cheese, onion and peppers. Pour remaining batter over the top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into wedges to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blackberry cobbler or 1 hour fruit cobbler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring berries and 1 cup of sugar to a boil.
Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sweet dough in pan.
Pour fruit over this.
Bake at 400° until browned on top, approximately 45 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Place in bottom of baking dish.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, salt and lemon juice. Mix well.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Add sour cream, soda and flour. Mix well. Add walnuts and strawberries. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Best bread in the south!

title: sunflower corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine milk, brown sugar, maple flavoring and muffin mix in a bowl and stir just until moist. Divide batter evenly among 12 muffin cups coated with cooking spray and sprinkle with sunflower seeds. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove muffins from pan immediately and place on a wire rack.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Boil the shrimp in about 2 quarts water and vinegar for 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain shrimp and place in a bowl of cold water. Add 1 sliced lemon (don't squeeze).
Let stand for 15 to 60 minutes.

title: southwestern rice and bean salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pepperidge farm sandwiches
directions: Blend margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix together ham and cheese.
Mix these 2 mixtures together.
Cut rolls in half.
Spread mixture on rolls.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli salad for 12
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Dice and add celery, green onions and eggs.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Toss and refrigerate.

title: cranberry sweet tart
directions: Place washed cranberries in a 9-inch glass, non-greased pie dish.
Pour 1/3 cup white sugar and 1 tablespoon of butter over top.
Cover with a moist paper towel.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients, except the walnuts.
Sprinkle walnuts over cooked berries and pour sugar mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top looks dry.
Serves 8 (or 1 if it's a hit).

title: homemade fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cream, butter and vanilla in a pot.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
When boil starts, time 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn off fire and mix in chocolate chips, peanut butter, pecans and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Put mixture on a flat pan with foil at bottom.
Work fast because mixture may get hard in pot.
For faster results, put into refrigerator.
Cut into squares before it gets too hard.

title: drunkin wienies
directions: Mix all together in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick baked stew
directions: Shake steak pieces in flour and brown in shortening. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour bouillon over. Stir. Cover and bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: pecan bar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add egg yolk, cinnamon and flour.
This will seem dry, but keep working.
Press into bottom of 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Spread beaten egg white on top.
Spread pecans evenly on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars.

title: homemade condensed milk
directions: One large "good morning" mixed with a spoonful of gladness. Stir in a few good laughs.
Put them in a pan full of thankfulness and bake for a night of rest and sweet dreams.
Serve with a prayer on a tray of sunbeams.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix together melted margarine, sugar, brown sugar, flour, vanilla, lemon juice and egg. Place apples in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar. Cut crust from bread, then cut bread in strips. Place strips very close together over apples. Spoon mixed ingredients over bread. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into flour, using a fork.
Stir in buttermilk. Roll (by hand) the dough into 15 large biscuits.
Handle dough lightly, adding flour as needed.
Bake in a hot oven (450°) until golden brown (about 15 minutes).
Serve hot with butter, honey, preserves or gravy.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice off bottoms of squash halves to level.
Brush inside with maple syrup.
Dot with butter. Bake miniature squash for 20 minutes, medium squash 35 to 45 minutes, until fork-tender.
Remove from oven and set aside. Increase oven temperature to 400°.
Cut sweet potatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Boil for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
In processor, combine sweet potatoes, cream, eggs, brown sugar, bourbon and spices.
Puree for 30 to 60 seconds.
Pour mixture into squash halves set in a buttered round baking dish.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 400° until set and puffy, 8 to 10 minutes for smaller squash, 15 to 20 minutes for larger.
Serve hot from oven. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mock spinach souffl
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; beat well. Stir in spinach. Spoon half of spinach mixture in a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with artichoke hearts. Cover with remaining mixture. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yield: About 8 servings. Easy and delish!

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Put in mixing bowl.
Combine sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes and cool slightly.
Pour over kraut.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Chill overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Make well in dry ingredients and add eggs, liquid and pumpkin. Add nuts, if desired.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add to
mixture and mix well.
Roll into long rolls. Refrigerate at least overnight.
They should be rolled in aluminum foil while refrigerated.
When ready to bake, take out one roll at a time.
Cut in slices and bake at 350° until done, approximately 10 minutes.
Will appear a little undone.
This makes a big batch.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl until smooth, 1 minute or more. Pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until tests done.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In heavy skillet, cook onions in bacon drippings until brown. Remove onions from pan.
Add beef and more bacon drippings, if necessary.

title: sausage bread
directions: Remove casing from sausage and fry until cooked. Remove sausage from frying pan and drain on paper towels.
Let pizza dough rise according to package directions.
Chop sausage into bite-size pieces.
Mix sausage and grated Mozzarella cheese together.
Roll dough into oval, approximately 12 x 10-inches. Fill lengthwise with sausage mixture, fold over and pinch seams where joined.
Place, seam side down, on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam, approximately 45 minutes at 350°.
Halfway through cooking, beat egg and brush over loaf to make it golden brown.

title: chicken ortega
directions: Pound breasts until thin; dip each in melted butter and then roll in crumb mixture.
Place a strip of Jack cheese and green chile on each breast and roll up and secure with toothpick.
Place in a greased oblong dish.
Drizzle butter over each breast.
Bake, uncovered, about 50 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
Looks very pretty and fancy.

title: holiday ham ball
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2-inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm. Makes about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: plain cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla. Beat on No. 2 speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl while beating. Stop mixer.
Scrape beaters.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat on No. 2 speed for 2 minutes longer, scraping bowl while beating.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from pans.
Cool.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs and oil, in a large mixing bowl.
In a small bowl beat the eggs and oil.
Pour the egg mixture over the flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes (at least).
Invert on rack; turn top side up.

title: onion cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook onions in melted margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients together, but reserve half of the cheese. Add cooked onions.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix ingredients and chill in refrigerator.
Divide dough in 2 parts.
Roll out like pie crust and line the bottom of a 10 x 15 inch pan.
Sprinkle crust with 2 handfuls of corn flakes.

title: rich homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until they begin to thicken.
Add Eagle Brand milk, whipping cream, and half 'n' half.
Add flavors of choice:
vanilla, crushed fruit, chocolate, etc.
Put in ice cream can* and freeze.

title: *instant salad
directions: Mix with spoon the cottage cheese and the carton of prepared whip.
Drain the canned fruit and blend the fruit into the cottage cheese; whip mixture.
Sprinkle jello right from the package and blend in to color.
Save a few sprinkles to accent the top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze water out and then mix with rest of ingredients.
Put in refrigerator to chill, then shape into walnut-size balls.
Quick freeze on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
You can keep in freezer bags until ready to bake for up to 1 month.
Makes 60.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Warm cream and butter on low just to boiling point, but do not allow to boil.
Add grated cheese and stir until creamy.
May leave on low until needed for pasta.

title: barbecue meat
directions: Combine these ingredients and let simmer while you dice cooked beef or pork roast.
Chuck roast is delicious this way.
Add meat and let simmer until well mixed.
Good to serve either on buns or over rice.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions until just tender. Drain.
Mix macaroni and remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cranberry-raisin sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Spoon over ham when serving.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Toss fruit lightly with 1 cup of the sugar.
Set aside.
Melt butter in deep baking pan or glass dish in a 350° oven.
Stir together remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and salt; pour over melted butter.
Do not stir!
Put sweetened fruit on top of batter.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.
(The batter will rise to the top during baking.) Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice steak into narrow strips.
Brown in the oil.
Combine with garlic, salt, pepper, soy sauce and sugar.
Cook on low in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn to high.
Add bean sprouts, tomatoes and pepper.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; stir into pot. Cover and cook on high 15 to 20 minutes or until thickened. Sprinkle with onions.
May serve over rice.
Suitable for freezing.

title: stewed prunes
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine prunes and lemon.
Cover with enough cold water and bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for about 40 minutes.
Add more water and sugar to taste.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars. Blend in peanut butter, egg and vanilla. Stir in flour, salt and baking soda. Roll in 1-inch balls and place in mini muffin tin. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven; press peanut butter cup into center of each cookie. Cool 10 minutes at room temperature. Remove from tins and place in refrigerator for 30 minutes to set.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oleo and sugar; mix well.
Chill, if desired.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 12 minutes (possibly 10); remove immediately.

title: uptown barbecue-style barbecue sauce
directions: Combine vinegar with salt, pepper, pepper flakes and molasses. Stir to blend well.
Let stand 4 hours for flavors to meld, then serve.

title: mom's custard
directions: Add eggs to cold milk.
Cook in heavy pan and stir constantly until steamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Cook and stir until custard coats a silver spoon (serve in cups).

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and butter; add water and bouillon cubes.
Boil and gradually add noodles and salt.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook for 3 minutes. Add milk, cheese and pepper. Stir constantly until cheese melts. Will freeze up to 1 month.

title: pistachio squares
directions: Mix.
Chill a few minutes.
Spread pudding on top of cream cheese mixture and top with the rest of the Cool Whip.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: oriental noodle soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine chicken broth, chicken, sugar and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles and peas.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes or until noodles and peas are tender.
Garnish each serving with green onions.
Makes 5 (1 1/2-cup) servings.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese into bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with both cans of chili.
Sprinkle diced green chiles over the chili.
Shred cheese and cover mixture.
Sprinkle olives on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until mixture is melted and bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips.
You may substitute Neufchatel cheese for the cream cheese for a lower calorie version.

title: dancing mothballs
directions: Put in large glass bowl or brandy snifter.
Add mothballs. Watch them dance.
Do not eat.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Drain pineapple and place in baking dish.
Pour flour and sugar mixture over pineapple. Cover with cheese and coarsely crushed crackers.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Combine water, sugar and cherries.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir into Jell-O until dissolved.
Add cola and pineapple (undrained).
Chill.

title: scotch broth
directions: Simmer lamb, barley and water for about 2 hours.
Cut and trim meat from bones.
Discard bone and return meat to soup.
Add vegetables and thyme; cook slowly for an hour.
Mix flour with cold water and blend into soup to thicken.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and eggs thoroughly.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips or brown sugar and nuts on top of batter and bake as directed on box.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, cocoa and egg and beat well for five minutes (do not underbeat).
Add buttermilk or sour milk and vanilla and mix.
Add flour, salt and baking soda and mix.
When thoroughly blended, add chunky chocolate or chocolate chips.

title: sauerbraten a la wenonah
directions: Mix vinegar, chili sauce, brown sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Add brisket.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight, turning brisket over once.
Place meat in 4 to 5-quart casserole.
Pour marinade over meat.
Top with onions.
Pour in water.
Cover and bake 2 hours, basting twice.
Remove cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes more, until meat is fork-tender.
Let stand 10 minutes and slice.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; refrigerate until needed.
In small saucepan, combine gelatin, brown sugar, salt and spice, mixing well.
Add molasses, egg yolks, milk and pumpkin, mixing well. Bring to boiling, stirring; remove from heat.
Transfer to medium bowl; cool, then refrigerate, covered, until firm.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Prepare shell.
Flute edges.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt. Stir in pumpkin, eggs, corn syrup and vanilla.
Turn into pie shell topping with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Bring to boil sugar, milk and margarine. Gradually add milk mixture to eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Put in large pie crust.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: adam's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook meat; debone and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook noodles.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Put into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: coconut icing(for moist cake)
directions: Thaw coconut and place between paper towels to help absorb excess moisture.
Mix with sour cream and sugar.
Poke small holes in cake before icing.
Spread icing over cake.
This icing is good on a devil's food or yellow cake.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve with fruit pieces.
Can use with bananas, apples, strawberries, grapes and candied cherries.
Use lemon juice for your fruit so it will stay pretty and fresh looking.

title: rice dressing
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions, adding bouillon cubes to cooking water.
Meanwhile, saute celery, onion and liver in butter.
Combine this with cooked rice, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Stuff and roast turkey.
Yield:
8 cups, enough for 8 to 10 pound turkey.

title: vanilla sugar wafers
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add egg, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Dip small glass bottom or round object into cold water and then into sugar or sugar-cinnamon mixture and use to press cookie dough into flat cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and water. Remove from heat. Add tea bags and cloves. After 5 minutes remove tea bags and cloves. Add lemon juice and orange juice.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Combine flour with Italian dressing, dehydrated tomato soup, pepper, salt, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Place all ingredients in a Ziploc bag and shake very well.
Heat vegetable oil in a frying pan over medium fire.
Place chicken parts in ingredients and shake bag until chicken parts are covered, then place in frying pan.
Serve with your favorite vegetable.

title: chunky chocolate chip - bears
directions: Mix in a bowl.
Pour into a greased pan and cook at 350°.

title: mint fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a heavy 3-quart saucepan; bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cover and boil 3 minutes.
Remove lid; cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage or candy thermometer registers 234°.
Remove from heat; cool 10 minutes.
Add butter and 1/4 teaspoon peppermint extract; beat until mixture thickens and begins to lose its gloss.
Pour mixture into a buttered 8-inch square baking pan or dish.
Cool and cut into squares.
Place squares at least 1/2 inch apart on a wax paper lined baking sheet; set aside.
Combine 1 cup powdered sugar and remaining ingredients, stirring until blended.
Place mixture in a heavy-duty, zip-top plastic bag; seal.
Snip a tiny hole in one corner of bag; drizzle over fudge.

title: sid's sausage(makes 100 pounds)
directions: Grind meat with seasonings.
Chill overnight.
Stuff and smoke for 4 hours with mesquite and pecan wood.
Wrap and freeze.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter and add to flour mixture.
Add brown sugar.
When mixture is crumbly, take out 1 cup and add cinnamon to this.
Mix well beaten egg, milk and water.
Stir into flour mixture.
Do not mix until smooth.
Put into a greased 9X9X2 baking pan and sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake about 25 minutes or until cake shrinks from pan.

title: savory rice(for microwave)
directions: Put ingredients in a micro-safe bowl.
Cook, covered, on High (100% power) for 3 to 5 minutes or until boiling.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Stir to fluff.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with sauerkraut and pour on dressing; top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, covered with foil entire cooking time.
Before serving, sprinkle top with parsley.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt
oleo
in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Spread ingredients
by layers in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender; drain well and pat dry with paper towels.
Arrange on bottom of a 2-quart (7 x 11-inch) buttered rectangular casserole.
Place chicken on top of broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine melted butter and bread crumbs and put on top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "nanny's" fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper each piece
of chicken after cutting it up. Mix egg and flour to make a wet batter and add chicken to it. Stir it well
until
each
piece
is
coated with the wet batter. May add a little water or milk to make it more moist. Be sure that the
chicken is well coated with batter.
Drop in hot Mazola oil in frying
pan
on medium heat and cook on each side 15 minutes until
brown.
Do not use deep oil, only about 1/2 of chicken should be in oil.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda in a large mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, blend margarine, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Mix well.
Pour over sugar and flour in bowl.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Blend well by hand or use mixer.
Bake in an 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop all vegetables and sprinkle with salt; let set overnight. Next day, rinse and drain vegetables.
Pour vinegar, sugar and water over vegetables with pickle spice (wrapped in cheesecloth). Bring to a boil.
Boil slow for ten minutes.
Put in hot jars.

title: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well. Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.

title: quick golden stew
directions: In a large saucepan, add enough water to cover carrots, potatoes and onions.
Cover; cook 10 minutes.
Add peas and hot dogs.
Continue cooking an additional 5 minutes; drain and stir in soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a mixer until crumbly. Press into a 9 x 13 cake pan. In a separate bowl, combine the confectioners sugar, cream cheese and eggs. Pour over first layer, spreading evenly. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until nicely browned. (Cake will fall.)

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, cabbage and onions.
Add a little canning salt and let stand overnight.
Drain off most of the juice, then add the apples, vinegar and sugar.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes. Pack into jars and water bath process.

title: k.f.c.  alike coleslaw
directions: Mix sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice; toss with cabbage and carrots.

title: curry fruit
directions: Heat butter.
Add brown sugar and curry powder.
Place fruit in baking dish; drizzle with butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese-bits(quick and delicious)
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cut slices in quarters.
Spread mixture of mayonnaise and cheese on bread.
Preheat oven to 450°. Place bread on a cookie sheet and bake in oven (do not use broiler).
Remove when brown, about 5 minutes.

title: hot ham & cheese sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together, spread on hot dog buns.
Wrap in foil. bake at 425 degrees for 10 minutes.
Watch closely as the buns burn easily.

title: kluski noodles
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Cut one large onion; saute in butter.
Add drained sauerkraut.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain and add to butter and onion mixture.
Add garlic salt to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking soda.
Add bananas to egg mixture. Stir.
Add flour to egg mixture.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Stir in nuts that have been lightly floured.
Bake 1 hour for a large loaf pan or 45 minutes for small loaf pan.

title: spiced tea
directions: Remove husks and silk from corn.
Wash ears and arrange in shallow glass baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High until corn is done, turning and rearranging ears once.
Cook 2 ears 7 to 9 minutes, 4 ears 11 to 12 minutes and 6 ears 14 to 16 minutes.
Corn steams nicely in a covered dish using microwave High setting.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Rub in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix in enough buttermilk to form soft dough.
(You may not need all milk.)
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead lightly until smooth.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/2 to 3/4-inch.
Cut out.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Cube potatoes, carrot and onion and boil in a large soup pot until tender (about 15 minutes).
Salt and pepper generously. Drain all but 1/2 cup of water off.
Add butter, milk, cream, the rest of the vegetables, about 1/2 teaspoon parsley and a dash of Italian season (or oregano).
Cook for 10 minutes, then test salt and pepper.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve with chunks of bread.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and beat well. Mix and add sour cream and baking soda. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture. Roll out on a lightly floured board and cut out. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: elegant sparkling punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 1 cup of the club soda; pour into punch bowl.
Add red wine and brandy, stirring well.
Add ice.
Pour in champagne and rest of club soda.
Add orange slices and berries. Serve immediately.

title: good 4 u punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid following package.
Pour 3 ounces orange juice and 3 ounces Kool-Aid and a big splash of diet 7-Up.
Red Kool-Aid works best.

title: microwave iced tea
directions: Take one gallon size tea bag (Tetley works best) and cover with 12 ounces of water.
Microwave on High for four minutes.
Let sit for five minutes.
Pour into six cups of water, sweetened with one cup sugar.
Cover the same tea bag with 12 ounces of water. Microwave on High for four minutes.
Let set for five minutes. Pour into first mixture.
Add six cups of water (no sugar).
Best if refrigerated overnight.
Makes 1 gallon of tea.

title: hot sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Grind with onions and hot peppers.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and bring to rolling boil.
Remove cover and allow to simmer boil for 2 hours or until thick.
Pour into scalded jars and seal.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Blend soup, milk and onion together. In a buttered casserole dish, arrange potatoes, soup mixture and cheese in layers, ending with cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla wafers.
Beat until mixed well; there will be small lumps.
Place a vanilla wafer in each muffin liner.
Fill with cream cheese mixture until 3/4 full. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate.
Top with your favorite canned fruit topping.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Heat to serving temperature and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 2-quart casserole.

title: walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In food processor, blend the eggs, maple syrup and tofu.
Add the vanilla extract and salt.
Put walnuts in bottom of crust.
Pour in egg mixture.
Place in oven for 30 minutes until center is firm. Allow to cool before cutting.

title: peanut butter fudge(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa and boil without stirring, until candy forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from fire; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat with a fork until creamy.
Pour on a buttered dish and cut in squares immediately.

title: two crust chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken in broth with onion and celery for 30 minutes. Remove chicken.
Put vegetables in broth; simmer 20 minutes.
Dice chicken; add soup and peas.
Drain vegetables.
Add to mixture. Pour in crust (only liquid is soup).
Invert other crust and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Fill well-greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: ground beef supper(low calorie)
directions: Cook meat until brown.
Remove any fat.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste.
Cover and simmer on low heat for about 40 minutes.
Stir often.
Makes 6 servings, 346 calories per serving.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Slice onions about 1/4-inch thick; separate the rings from each other and leave in cold salted water for 30 minutes.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and spices into 1 bowl.
Beat egg and water in another bowl.
Drain onions.
Dip first in crumb mixture, then egg mixture and then back in crumbs.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove foil and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until they reach desired crunchiness.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix rice, broccoli and soup together.
Put half of mixture in dish and sprinkle with 1/2 of the cheese.
Put the remainder of mixture in dish and put in the rest of the cheese.
Cover with a glass lid and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry winks(cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients; add nuts, dates and cherries.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls into crushed cornflakes.
Cover thoroughly.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Top each cookie with 1/4 chopped cherry. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.
Delicious as well as pretty.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl. Beat about 5 minutes. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325 for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Boil oleo, shortening, cocoa and water together in a saucepan; bring to a good boil.
Then add eggs, vanilla, salt, buttermilk and soda.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix eggs, fruit cocktail and cake mix.
Don't drain fruit and don't use liquid called for on the cake mix box.
Mix as directed.
Bake as directed.
Use a Bundt pan or angel food pan. When cooled, glaze it with 3/4 cup powdered sugar and enough lemon juice to make it consistent.

title: oreo cookies
directions: First Layer:
Crumble Oreo cookies; melt margarine.
Mix together and layer in dish.

title: club chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add onion.
Stir until limp.
Add flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in broth, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly until thick.
Grease an 11 x 8-inch casserole.
Add rice; mix in chicken and pimiento.
Add sauce and mix.
Shake parsley over. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio inside outside cake
directions: Blend in large bowl the cake mix, 1 package pudding, 3 eggs, club soda, oil and nuts.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed. Bake in a greased, floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Split horizontally and fill with icing.

title: chicken carusa
directions: Brown chicken pieces in the oven or a skillet.
Put chicken in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: fudge nut sauce
directions: In a double boiler over hot water, melt margarine and chocolate chips, stirring until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Serve hot. May be refrigerated and reheated.
Makes 2 cups.

title: norine's apple dumplings
directions: Peel and slice apples into 8 slices each apple. Roll apple slices in crescent rolls.

title: cool raspberry soup
directions: In a blender, pure raspberries and water. Add juice, sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Remove from heat; strain and cool. Whisk in lemon juice and yogurt. Refrigerate. When ready to serve, pour in small bowls and top with dollop of sour cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook all of the above until the liquid has cooked out (use just enough water to cook this).
This is very good to eat as a vegetable at this stage.

title: molded cranberry waldorf salad and dressing
directions: Heat 1 cup cranberry juice just to boiling and pour over jello to dissolve.
Add 1 cup cranberry juice and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into molds or square pan to chill.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put layer of chips in buttered casserole.
Add rest of ingredients.
Top with remainder of chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: damn hot chili
directions: Heat shortening (1 tablespoon) in pot.
Add meat and garlic. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add to meat and stir well to coat meat thoroughly.
Stir in tomato sauce, beer and water.
Prick jalapenos and drop them in whole.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: oven goulash
directions: Combine all ingredients except the French fried onions.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: strawberry cake(lm-will's special)
