directions: Mix oil, eggs and cake mix and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Mix flour and Jell-O and set aside.
Drain strawberries.
Add strawberries and Jell-O mixture to cake mix mixture and beat 1 minute.
Pour into a greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes for layer cake.
Bake approximately 45 minutes for Bundt.

title: mint brownies
directions: Make brownie mix and pour half in bottom of pan.
Place peppermint patties about 3/4 inch apart on top of brownie patties. Bake at temperature and time specified for brownie mix.
Let cool and serve.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix together frozen lemonade and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Can use graham cracker crust if you prefer.
Refrigerate.

title: applesauce spice bread(mr. hendrickson's favorite)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Blend well, then beat at medium speed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
tags: Jell-O brand vanilla flavor instant pudding

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix mustard, celery seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion together.
Place ham and cheese on buns individually.
Spoon some of the mustard mixture on each bun.
Wrap each sandwich in a square of foil and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: fruited cheese ball
directions: Soak apricots 1 minute in hot water and cut up (use scissors). Cream the cream cheeses together and add other ingredients. Chill well in refrigerator.
Form into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with thin gingersnaps.
Delicious!

title: confetti coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrot; sprinkle with salt and sugar. Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and milk; mix well.
Add apple just before serving.

title: mom's candied yams
directions: Slice potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except banana, and whisk until just blended.
Fold in banana slices.
Cook on lightly oiled or buttered pan.
Yields 8 to 12, approximately 4 inches.

title: zucchini pitas(quick and easy open pockets)
directions: Squeeze the insides out of sausages and brown.
Add to can of zucchini mix with pepper and garlic salt, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Grate cheese.
Split pitas in half, then scoop mix into pitas and top with cheese.
Add other spices per taste.

title: the state cookie of texas
directions: In a large bowl, cream the oleo and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and oats.
Add to creamed mixture and mix until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Use Texas shaped cookie pan.
Line with aluminum foil.
Spread cookie dough over whole pan, pressing to flatten.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 28 minutes.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Mix soup, water and rice in baking pan.
Put chicken pieces on top, then sprinkle onion soup on top.
Seal foil over top of pan. There is no need to peek.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: penny punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water and slices of orange and mix well.
Chill until cool (15 to 20 minutes).
Add ginger ale and ice cubes just before serving.
Makes 2 quarts or 16 servings.

title: hot italian cold cut sandwiches
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, basil, oregano and garlic powder together in jar or bowl until well blended.
Spread inside of each roll with thin layer of mayonnaise.
Drizzle each with a little of oil & vinegar mixture.
Layer each roll with meats and onion.

Place a slice of cheese on top of meat and on inside top half of roll. Place filled rolls on a ungreased baking sheet or broiler pan. Broil for 3-5 minutes or until cheese is melted and golden - do not burn.
Remove sandwiches and add additional mayonnaise and dressing if desired, lettuce leaves and tomato.
Serve hot.

title: apple jelly pie(from the kitchen of carolyn norman)
directions: Beat butter and sugar together well.
Add egg yolks (well beaten).
Beat well again.
Add apple jelly.
Beat until well blended.
Add milk and vanilla.
Put in pastry shell and bake until firm in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until a silver knife comes out clean.
Beat egg whites and put on top and brown. Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie and 1 (4-inch) pie.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in 1/2-inch slices and cook until almost done. Drain and place in a casserole dish.
Melt oleo; add soup, parsley flakes, sour cream and part of the cheese and heat.
Pour the mixture over the potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes and the rest of the grated cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven until bubbly hot, about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in oblong buttered glass baking dish.
Bake at 400° until nice and brown (about 35 minutes).

title: yellow pistachio cake
directions: Use a coffee cup to measure.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and then add last 2 ingredients.
Bake at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small, greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Grease pan and pour in ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Makes 10-inch pie.

title: brass and copper cleaner
directions: Brush on with toothbrush.
Let set 2 hours.
Wash off with water.
Buff with steel wool.
Coat with acrylic lacquer or tongue oil.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Do not use whisk or mixer!
In saucepan put margarine and sugar.
Stir over medium heat until it simmers.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add well beaten eggs, a small amount at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a well-greased and floured 12 x 16-inch pan or two smaller ones.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in 1-inch squares while still warm.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cake: Combine all the ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Remove from oven and cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until very hot.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: multi layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a large bowl. Make dressing.

title: dancer's quick snack
directions: Spread butter over sliced bread.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over bread.
Place in microwave for 40 to 45 seconds.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook onions and butter until done.
Bring water, bouillon cubes and noodles to a boil.
Cook 3 minutes; add broccoli.
Cook for 5 minutes; add milk and cheese.
Bring to a boil and turn off.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: In Dutch oven or large kettle, brown ground beef and drain well.
Add potatoes, onion and tomato sauce.
Stir in water, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and soup has thickened.
Sprinkle parsley flakes 15 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings or 2 quarts.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken and tear into bite size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients with a mixer and pour over torn up chicken.
Pour 1/4 cup melted oleo over.
Add crushed cracker crumbs to cover. Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: tropical cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 or 10-inch pie plate with a nonstick vegetable spray and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, milk, egg substitute, margarine and pudding mix. Using an electric mixer, beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into the prepared pie plate.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, celery, onions, mayonnaise, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a greased pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, bread crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until good and brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put into baking dish.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Work together real good.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes.
Pack tightly in jars.
Fill with boiling water and seal.
Make in a full moon.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in 1/2 cup butter.
Add soup, Tabasco, soy sauce, salt and pepper. Stir and simmer.
Cook beans; drain.
Add to first mixture.
Stir in water chestnuts.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes or until top bubbles.

title: quick garden cheese soup(makes about 2 quarts)
directions: In large kettle, cook celery and onion in margarine or butter until tender; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then bouillon, pepper and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot (do not boil).
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain off water and mash.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add squash.
Place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until set.

title: fudge cake
directions: Heat chocolate with water over very low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with fudge frosting.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour; brown in hot fat.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour into baking pan.
Add chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese fondue
directions: In saucepan, heat milk and margarine together until margarine melts.
In electric blender container, combine flour, cheese that has been cut up in cubes and the onion soup mix that has soaked in the water a few minutes.
Add hot milk/margarine into the blender container.
Cover and process at liquefy until smooth.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix well and use with Bugles or other crackers.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together gelatin, water, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Cool slightly and add onions, celery, cottage cheese and spinach.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, salt and cold milk.
Add scalded milk and stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: fancy franks
directions: Cut hot dogs in bite size pieces.
Blend remaining ingredients in skillet.
Stir until hot dogs are coated.
Heat, covered, over low heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Cut each chicken breast half into 8 pieces.
Mix oil, garlic and pepper.
Combine bread crumbs and cayenne pepper and place on plate.
Roll chicken nuggets in bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet in a single layer.
Bake 15 minutes or until browned and done.
Dip nuggets in honey and mustard sauce.

title: plain candy
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Cook
until sugar dissolves and forms
a
firm
ball
when dropped into cold water. Remove from heat
and
beat until cool enough to hold in hand. Add chopped nuts.
Pour out on greased cookie sheet.

title: brie cheese appetizer
directions: Cut top off cheese, just the rind and then place in a shallow baking dish.
In a medium saucepan, melt the margarine and brown sugar.
Add the almonds.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Place dish on middle rack of oven and broil for 5 to 7 minutes, watching carefully as not to burn.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding by box directions.
Line bottom and sides of baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Add 1/3 of the banana slices and top with 1/3 of the pudding.
Repeat again.
Then refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut bell peppers in half.
Boil bell peppers for 30 minutes. Place bell peppers in baking dish.
Mix in bowl meat, onion, tomato sauce and rice.
Fill peppers.
Pour a little of sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips in crock-pot and heat until cheeses are melted and all is well mixed and softened.
Dip chips.
Great appetizer.

title: delicious cabbage slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate to let flavors blend.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: coffee cake(serves 12)
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, sour cream and eggs until well blended.
Mix cinnamon, pecans and brown sugar.
Pour 1/2 of first mixture in Bundt or angel food pan and add half of cinnamon, pecans and brown sugar mixture.
Add other 1/2 of cake mixture and other 1/2 of icing and swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 80 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hidden valley oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch mix with dill weed and garlic powder. Then add salad oil and mix.	Pour over crackers and stir to coat.
Place in warm oven at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently halfway through baking.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in lightly greased 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: georgia candy cookies
directions: Blend 2 butters in bowl; work in 10x sugar with wooden spoon until combined, then add graham crackers to mixture.
Press mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan evenly.
Melt chocolate and put quickly over top of cookie.
Place into refrigerator until firm.
As soon as chocolate is cool, 30 to 45 minutes, cut into squares.

title: broccoli, bacon and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower and cheese in large covered bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk; add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip. Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Add remainder of Cool Whip on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil, then remove from heat. Add 6 ounces (1 cup) chocolate morsels and vanilla extract.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Put reserved pineapple juice in small saucepan.
To this, add the next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat and cool.
Combine in a salad bowl the pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges and bananas.
Mix the whipped cream with cooled sauce.
Fold into fruit.
Chill for several hours.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of pan (9 1/2 x 11 pan). Spread cake mix over pie filling. Melt and put butter over cake mix. Bake until brown.

title: delicious cold italian pasta salad
directions: Dice cucumbers, tomatoes and green onions.
Slice black olives.
Mix vegetables together.
Cook and cool noodles.
Mix all ingredients.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn into shallow glass casserole.
Bake for 1 hour. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, Bisquick, vegetables and cheese.
Grease 7 x 11-inch baking dish or a jelly roll pan may be used if using for hors d'oeuvres.
Add mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes if using jelly roll pan.

title: stew beef casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together well in casserole dish.
Cover. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into a saucepan; add jello and marshmallows to the juice.
Heat on low flame until marshmallows are melted.
Let cool, then add rest of the ingredients and chill until set.
Serve on lettuce leaf or shredded lettuce.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease a large, deep pie plate.
Put the raw cranberries in the plate.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and the pecans over the cranberries.
Mix 1 cup sugar, melted butter, liquid shortening, eggs and flour. Pour over cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: cheesy olive wedges
directions: Mix all ingredients, except English muffins.
Chill.
Spread thickly on split muffins.
Cut each half muffin into 4 pieces. Bake at 375° on cookie sheet until brown, about 10 minutes. (These can be frozen before baking.)
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hamburger pizza
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add eggs, tomato paste, ketchup or barbecue sauce, milk and seasoning to taste. Press down crescent rolls into a pie pan.
Put hamburger mixture into the pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for at least 30 minutes.
Put cheese topping on
for the last 15 minutes.

title: millet stuffed peppers(a vegetarian main course)
directions: Rinse millet.
Put into heavy bottomed saucepan with tomatoes, chicken, broth, onion, garlic and spices.
Cook over low heat with cover, about 25 minutes.
At about 20 to 22 minutes, stir and check to see if most grains are "popped".
(Remove garlic.)

title: chow chow
directions: Grind tomatoes, onion and pepper; drain juice.
Put spices in cheesecloth bag.
Add remaining ingredients and boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: lickin good salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add sugar and let stand until gelled.
Beat Dream Whip; beat in jello and cream cheese.
Fold in nuts, cherries and pineapple.
Let set 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: broccoli grape salad
directions: Wash broccoli, peel stems and chop in bite size pieces, using broccoli flowers as well.
Chop or slice grapes in half.
For added color use red grapes or mix with white grapes.
Combine broccoli and grapes.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar.
Pour over broccoli and grapes.
Store in refrigerator.
Just before serving, stir salad.

title: cornish hen
directions: Cut Cornish hen in half down middle of breast.
Spread hen in an oblong Pyrex dish or small baking pan.
In the preheated toaster oven or regular oven, bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven, boney side up.

title: mud cake
directions: Cream 2 sticks melted butter, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, coconut and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven promptly.
While hot, spread marshmallow cream on top of baked cake.
Let cool before frosting.

title: microwave old-fashioned bread pudding(a baked custard dessert)
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Beat with rotary beater.
Stir in bread cubes and raisins.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Microwave uncovered for 26 to 28 minutes on simmer or until almost set in center.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Delicious!

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Add powdered sugar and graham crackers.
Spread mixture out into a cookie sheet pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 3/4-inch size.
Melt chips and spread over mixture.
Refrigerate until hardened.
Cut into squares.

title: "hello dollies"
directions: Melt
oleo
in large square cake pan.
Cover the bottom of pan with
graham
cracker
crumbs.
Layer
the rest of the ingredients,
pouring
can of condensed milk on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Wait until cool to slice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Cook until tender in salt water. Drain thoroughly.
Add margarine and mash squash and onion until very fine.
Add crumbled crackers, egg, 1/2 cup milk and sugar; mix well.
Add cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole and cook 1 hour at 300°.
Add 1/3 cup cracker crumbs and pats of margarine to top and allow to remain in oven until crumbs are brown and crisp.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt together the chocolate and butterscotch chips with peanut butter.
Put 1/2 the mixture in a waxed-paper lined jellyroll pan (11 x 17) and refrigerate.
To the other half, add the peanuts; set aside.

title: zucchini carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until frothy.
Gradually beat in oil. Add dry ingredients, beating on high speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in carrot, nuts and zucchini.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.

title: crab pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: smoked salmon-parsnip rounds
directions: Preparation:
Peel and coarsely grate parsnips into a bowl. Grate in apple and onion.
Toss and sprinkle on flour.
Lightly beat the eggs and add.
Add salt and pepper and toss to combine well.

title: "designer" crayons
directions: Remove paper wrappers from crayons.

Break crayons into pieces and put them into empty baby food jars, separating the colors. Fit a small rack inside a saucepan and place the jars on the rack. Fill the saucepan with enough water to cover 1/2-inch of the jars.
Heat the water until crayons melt.
Pour the melted wax into a plastic candy mold tray (available at craft supply stores in a variety of fun shapes and holiday shapes).
The wax will harden quickly and pop out of the mold easily.

title: carl's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs, peanut butter and vanilla together until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and salt to cream.
Shape into balls size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake 7 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: italian dressing
directions: Place all the ingredients into a 1/2-pint screw-top jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously to blend.
Store the dressing in the refrigerator and shake well before each use.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: white bean tuna salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. Gradually whisk in oil. In a large bowl, combine the beans, tuna, olives and onions. Add dressing and toss gently. Refrigerate until served. Yield: 6 servings.

title: corny rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute the red pepper, onion and jalapeno in oil until tender. Add the rice, corn, salt and pepper. Cook and stir until heated through. Sprinkle with green onions. Serve with soy sauce, if desired. Yields 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Drain.
Add soups, 2 cans water and tomato paste.
Heat until bubbly.
Turn off heat and add sour cream.
Mix well.
Serve over hot cooked shell noodles.

title: quick beanie weenies
directions: Microwave Directions:
Chop hot dogs into bite-size pieces and add all ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir, then cook an additional 2 minutes.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage and remove from pot.
Saute onions and garlic in 1 tablespoon of sausage drippings.
Add broth through sausage. Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Skim the fat from the top of the soup.
Stir in zucchini through the pepper.
Simmer covered for 35 to 40 minutes until the tortellini are tender.
Serve with Parmesan sprinkled on top.

title: flat bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide dough into balls; roll out each ball until very thin.
Bake.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Peel and dice.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook for one minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture is thickened.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onions, 1/2 cup crumbled bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk if soup is too thick.
Pour in individual soup bowls.
Top with pinch of green onions, bacon and cheese.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stuff bird with dressing.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture.
If you prefer you can add only half of the M & Ms and save the other half for decorating.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake for 10-12 min. Do not over bake and cool for 2 min. before removing from cookie sheet.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Place berries in pan.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Mix well and sprinkle over berries.
Dot with butter.
Cover with pastry.
Trim edges and seal.
Make several slits in top to allow steam to escape.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: btc sandwiches
directions: Place
thin
slice
of
tomato on toasted bread.
Add 1 layer of
bacon
slices
and 1 layer of sliced cheese.
(Most people can eat at least
2 of these or more if you're good and hungry.) Place on
a
biscuit pan and broil until cheese melts and browns slightly.

title: apple cider chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces; pat dry.
Shake,
a few at a time, in 4 tablespoons of the flour,
in
a
paper bag, to coat well (save remaining flour for
later).
Brown
chicken
slowly
in salad oil in a large
frying
pan; remove from pan.
Set aside for later.

title: pineapple-vanilla chess pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked, 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until firm when shaken.

title: jewish pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, extract and eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Place mixture in angel food pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two 8-inch pans with waxed paper. Butter and flour pans.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in corn syrup and mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into prepared pans and bake 30 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Remove from pans, slice into squares and serve.

title: pink lemonade ice cream loaf
directions: Slice cake into 3 layers.
Combine ice cream and lemonade. Spread half of ice cream mixture on bottom layer of cake.
Top with second layer and spread with rest of mixture.
Place 3rd layer on top and freeze for 30 minutes.
Beat whipped cream (if using).
Add powdered sugar and beat well.
Frost top and sides. Freeze until firm.
Slice and serve with strawberries.

title: bean chowder
directions: When beans are half done, add salt, chili seasoning, onions, garlic and tomato sauce.
Cook until done.
Stir in ground beef which has been browned.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beef tips in crockpot
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
The combine the beef tips, mushroom and onion soups in crock pot and let simmer all day.
Just before serving add the sour cream.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: faith's peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter, add peanut butter and slowly add confectioners sugar.
Roll into small balls and freeze.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, syrup, salt, and vanilla. Spread nuts in bottom and pour in filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: tasty appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oil and broth.
Shape into small 1-inch meatballs.
Preheat frypan on high setting for 10 to 12 minutes.
Lightly brush frypan with oil.
Add half of meatballs and fry until lightly browned, turning occasionally.
When meatballs are brown, remove and repeat with remaining half. Drain. Return all meatballs to frypan.
Add broth to frypan.
Cover and turn frypan temperature to low. Simmer for about 5 to 15 minutes or until coked through.
Serve on toothpick from frypan.
(These meatballs may be frozen for later use.) Makes 100 meatballs.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Prepare chicken bouillon and add potatoes, onion, carrot, celery, dill weed and seasoning.
Simmer for 1 hour until potatoes are tender.
Add sour cream, milk, cheese and instant potatoes to thicken.
Simmer until all ingredients are blended together.

title: barbara's creamed spinach
directions: Heat slowly the white sauce; add spinach and onion.
Stir until spinach is defrosted and serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Put into large casserole with salt and pepper.
In drippings, saute onions until brown.
Add mushrooms, cook 5 minutes.
Mix together tomato paste, flour, consomme, bay leaf and garlic.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda, cinnamon, apples in mixing bowl.
Combine sour cream, oil, egg, pecans, vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tin (3/4 full).
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool.

title: company casserole (meat casserole)
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onions.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper and Mrs. Dash.
Mix in both tomato sauces, tomato soup plus a little water and peas or corn.
Add noodles.
Makes a lot!
Place in casserole dishes.
Top with slices of Longhorn Cheddar cheese.
Cover; bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion chopped in it; drain.
Chop bell pepper; add with rest of ingredients.
Mix.
Put in casserole dish; bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly coat a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Slice the sweet potatoes by hand in very thin slices or use a food processor with a 2-millimeter disk.
In a large bowl, carefully toss the sweet potato slices by hand in the oil to coat the chips lightly.
Lay the slices in a single layer in the prepared baking pan.

title: coffee cake honey bun
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, sour cream, eggs and sugar and pour half batter in pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spread over first half.
Pour remaining batter over first layer in pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli squares
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Grind broccoli in food processor or blender.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is limp.
Combine eggs with bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, soup, herbs and broccoli.
Blend with the onion mixture and turn into greased 9-inch square baking pan; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until set.
Cool and refrigerate.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve either at room temperature or preheat for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Put the oatmeal, coconut or nuts and vanilla in a bowl.
Put the remaining ingredients in a pan.
Place pan on low heat; stir constantly and let boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour mixture over that in bowl.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let dry.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix the sour cream, Miracle Whip,
sugar, salt and pepper to make a dressing.
Layer the salad in a large casserole pan as follows:
lettuce, eggs, onions, bacon, peas, tomatoes, dressing and Swiss cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and let set while mixing cake.
Add egg yolks and mashed bananas and beat well.
Add milk alternately with sifted flour, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Finally, fold in egg whites that have been beaten stiff, but not dry.
Bake about 45 minutes in Bundt pan at 300°.
Can also make into two small loaves or in sheet pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: soubise
directions: Place salt in water; bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain and place in ovenproof casserole.
Melt butter in skillet; add onions and saute onions until soft.
Add to rice; stir.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; add sour cream, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper to taste. Good hot or cold.

title: fruited mint tea
directions: Pour boiling water over 12 mint sprigs and tea bags.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove and discard mint sprigs and tea bags, squeezing tea bags gently.
Add sugar, stirring until dissolved. Stir in cold water, orange juice and lemon juice.
Serve over ice. Garnish, if desired.
Yields about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Saute carrot and onion in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Add this to the broth.
Add the garlic and the rest of the ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add the cream.

title: turkey salad
directions: Whip mayonnaise and whipped cream together.
Combine all other ingredients and add whipped mixture.
Let set overnight or several hours before serving.
You may also add some seasoning salt, pepper, garlic salt and onion salt.

title: honey dew biscuits
directions: Mix well all ingredients together and bake in greased and floured muffin pans.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cukes and let stand overnight in cold water.
Pack jars with pickles, garlic, dill and red peppers.
Combine vinegar, salt and water.
Bring to full rolling boil and pour into jars.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast and 4 cups flour in a large bowl.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour.
Let rise (will rise in half the time).
Knead and form into rolls, using the amount of butter and cinnamon that suits your taste.
Let rise and bake at 400° to 425° for about 12 minutes.

title: old-fashioned pancakes
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix egg and milk. Add margarine or oil and add mixture to dry ingredients. Stir to blend. Fry on greased skillet. Turn when bubbles break and small holes remain.
Cakes are done when bottom is lightly browned.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil potatoes and mash.
Brown hamburger, drain and add the onion soup mix, golden mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Mix well.
Put mixture in bottom of a glass 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Put peas and carrots on top and add cheese and mashed potatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix apples and sugar in a large bowl.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Sift dry ingredients; mix with apples.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: country-style cole slaw
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan. Beat all ingredients except powdered sugar, milk and vanilla on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Pour in pan and bake about 50 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: egg kisses
directions: Have egg whites at room temperature.
Beat egg whites until they are very stiff.
Add the sifted sugar and salt very slowly, 1/2 teaspoon at a time.
Beat the eggs on high speed constantly. Add the vanilla.
Continue to beat for several minutes after the last of the sugar and vanilla have been added.
They should be very stiff.
Place by spoonfuls, depending on the size you want the kisses, on a large baking sheet that has been covered with brown paper.
Place in center of a 325° oven for 4 to 5 minutes. Turn off oven and leave kisses until oven is cool.
Egg Kisses may be made several days ahead.

title: cheese spread
directions: Melt all together in double boiler (do not cook).
Pour into airtight container.

title: potato wedges
directions: Thoroughly scrub as many medium to large sized potatoes as needed.
Cut
into quarters
or
halves, depending on size. Coat with flour.
Place in melted butter (enough to completely cover bottom
of dish) in baking dish.
(Single layer.) Sprinkle with seasoned salt and Parmesan cheese. Bake until done in 350°
oven, approximately
minutes.
Can
turn
half
way through baking if desired.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs and sauteed onion.
Add 3/4 of the grated cheese.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and poppy seed on top.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked whitefish with shrimp
directions: Rinse fish.
Pat dry.
With tweezers, pull out visible bones from ridge of fillets.
Melt butter in shallow baking dish.
Place fillets in pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salt.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until the fish flakes easily.
Pour cream into a saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer until reduced to about 3/4 cup.
Sprinkle shrimp over baked fish.
Pour hot cream evenly over all.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat until the cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with chopped basil or parsley.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water, no salt.
Save broth.
Melt margarine in pan; stir in stuffing mix.
Place one layer of stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole dish, then chicken that has been taken from bones and cubed.
Alternate layers of crumb mixture and chicken, ending with crumb mixture on top.
Mix chicken and mushroom soup with 2 cans of chicken broth.
Pour this over entire casserole slowly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Can make 2 small casseroles and freeze for later use.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fix instant rice in water and salt to boil.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender.

title: orange clove pie
directions: Mix nuts and raisins; place in the bottom of crust.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over nuts and raisins in shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: lime cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Press crumb mixture evenly over bottom and up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese at high speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in lime rind, juice and vanilla.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.
Combine sour cream and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Stir well and spread evenly over cheesecake.
Bake at 500°. Let cool to room temperature on a wire rack.
Chill at least 8 hours.
To serve, carefully remove sides of spring-form pan.
If desired, garnish with strawberries and lime slices.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper; drain grease.
Add all ingredients, except Doritos and cheese; mix well.
Place Doritos in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Add mixture and cheese, alternating until all are used up.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: salmonettes
directions: Drain the salmon; reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Put salmon into mixing bowl, breaking it apart with a fork.
Add flour and egg. Add pepper (no salt); mix well.
Add baking powder to reserved liquid; beat well with a fork until foamy.
Pour this into salmon mixture; stir until blended.
Using 2 teaspoons, scoop out the mixture with one and use the other to push the mixture off the teaspoon into a deep fryer that is half full of hot oil.
Watch closely; they brown fast.
Remove from hot oil; drain on paper towels.

title: for the bluebirds
directions: Mix the ingredients
together and place in bird feeder. This will attract real bluebirds.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese with dry Jell-O.
Add drained fruits. Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat soup; dissolve gelatine in water.
Add to soup.
Add cream cheese while soup is heating.
Stir or beat until smooth. Cool slightly (10 minutes in freezer).
Mix other ingredients in bowl.
Add soup mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spray bowl lightly with Pam and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: sourdough starter
directions: In a large pitcher, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of water.
Stir in remaining water, sugar and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Cover; let stand for 5 to 10 days, stirring 2 to 3 times a day and carefully recovering each time.

title: amish bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Add oil, baking powder, baking soda, eggs, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Bake as is or add 1 cup of nuts, raisins, diced apples, etc.
Grease and sugar two 8 1/2 x 3 3/4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Melt in double boiler.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Add to a pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, melt margarine.
Add rice.
Add soup and consomme.
Stir.
Place mushrooms on top of mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water and margarine.
Pour over oatmeal and let stand 10 minutes.
Add eggs, brown sugar and sugar; mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa; mix well.
Pour batter into greased cake pan.
Sprinkle rest of chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix as given.
Bake at 350°.
Check with toothpick to see when done.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: party punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a gallon container.
Finish filling container with water.
Best when refrigerated for at least 2 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Will serve approximately 25.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in greased tube pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Melt margarine in small saucepan; add cinnamon, sugar and nuts and cook on medium heat until mixture is bubbly.
Pour over rolls.
Cover pan tightly with foil and leave on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Turn out on plate.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake in 2 layers and cool, then split layers.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with 2/3 cup sugar plus salt, corn syrup and butter.
Add pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and half of the dry ingredients.
Add the rest with oatmeal, Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: alice merle's hush puppies
directions: Stir in enough water to mix thoroughly.
Drop the hush puppies by tablespoon into hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place vanilla wafers on bottom of paper cup liners.
Place in a muffin pan.
Top with filling.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate. Before serving, top with canned pie filling.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in shortening until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with water; stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon hot creole into center of parsley rice ring, made by combining 1/4 cup chopped parsley with 3 cups hot cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: golden coconut peach pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine peaches, sugar, flour, nutmeg, salt and juice.
Pour into pie shell; dot with butter. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over hot filling.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until the coconut is toasted, about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Pour ingredients into jar, then shake well. Pour over salad.

title: onion biscuits
directions: Add onion to butter.
Place biscuits on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a hollow in the center of each biscuit with the bottom of a small glass dipped in flour. Fill with onion butter mixture.
Bake in a very hot oven (450°) for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and flour.
Mix at medium speed until well blended (very stiff batter).
Add one egg at a time; mix well.
Add milk and mix.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 250° and bake for 40 minutes.
Loosen spring pan as soon as you take out of oven.

title: italian vegetable toss
directions: In a shallow 2-quart casserole, place zucchini, yellow squash, mushrooms, margarine, basil and pepper. Cover with a sheet of wax paper.
Microwave on High until squash is tender-crisp, 8 to 10 minutes, rotating halfway through cooking time.
Add tomato wedges and sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: challah
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water, mixing with a spoon to combine.
Add the sugar, oil, salt and the 3 beaten eggs, mixing well.
Add 4 cups of the flour, gradually beating into the mixture.
The batter will be lumpy and runny.
Add more flour, using the spoon to combine, until the dough is too thick to beat.
The dough should be stiff, but sticky.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Mix ingredients in ice cream pail and freeze. To serve fill glass half full with slush and add white soda till glass is full.

title: docksider's peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust.
Freeze and enjoy.
Easy.

title: wassail - crowd size(serve immediately.  serves 50 to 75 cups.)
directions: Pour apple cider and orange juice into a large coffee pot. Mix remaining ingredients and place in perk basket.
Let coffee pot perk as it would for coffee.
You may half ingredients for home 30-cup coffee maker.

title: breakfast blueberry muffins
directions: In medium bowl, thoroughly stir flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
In small bowl, beat eggs until foamy; add milk and margarine and beat to blend.
Add to flour mixture and stir only until it is moistened.
Fold in berries.
Fill greased muffin pan cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with topping (1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind, stirred together).
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dog-gone good pie
directions: In a bowl, mix together the softened margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; mix well.
Add drained crushed pineapple, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake until brown or until it will not wiggle.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients; beat until well blended.
Add hot milk.
Bake in well-greased floured pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: seafood in white wine broth
directions: In large kettle, bring 2 1/2 quarts water to boiling; add lobster tails, return to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered 8 minutes.
With slotted utensil, lift out lobster tails, and set aside until cool enough to handle.
Return water to boiling.
Add shrimp; return to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Drain crabmeat, removing any cartilage and leaving pieces as big as possible.
Remove meat from lobster shells; cut into bite-size pieces.
Melt butter in Dutch oven; remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, paprika and pepper until smooth.
Bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Add wine, stirring until well combined.
Add seafood; stir gently until combined.
Cook over low heat until heated through.
Do not boil.
Add more Half and Half if sauce is too thick.
Makes 12 servings.
Or use 2 cans (7 1/2 oz. size) king crab meat, drained.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil before adding to chicken.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix and press on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: king ranch doves
directions: Separate dove breast from bone.
Take dove breast, add a dab of cream cheese; lay on a sliver of jalapeno, then wrap in a strip of bacon.
Stick in a toothpick to hold together.
Grill outside and eat like popcorn.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients but cheese.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill.
Easy and delicious.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk, and pepper.
In a 2 1/2 quart baking dish, alternate layers of potatoes, onions, cheese, and soup mixture.
Dot top with butter.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more or until done.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In large size mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients. Turn mixture into pie shell. Bake in 375° oven until sharp knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes. Cool. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: clark bar cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix together using hands.
Press down firmly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tuna layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Spread on Miracle Whip, sealing edges.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crock-pot chicken licken
directions: Melt butter in pan and brown chicken well.
Remove chicken. Brown onion and garlic; add seasonings, tomatoes, soup and water. Place chicken in crock-pot.
Pour all other ingredients over chicken.
Cook 4 to 6 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Combine margarine, garlic and chives to make garlic sauce. Add cheese to sauce in pan.
Heat until cheese melts.
Place shrimp in baking dish and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 300° for 5 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thick. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello and lemon juice; mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten Milnot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Cream together with margarine and sugar.
Add syrup, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix in blender all ingredients except crackers.
Put crackers in a large plastic container and pour liquid over them.
Stir well until all liquid has been absorbed.
Keep covered with a tight lid.

title: crock pot beef stew
directions: Put all in crock pot and cook on low 6-8 hours.
(Do not dilute soups.)

title: old settler's baked beans(serves 12)
directions: Cook beef until lightly brown.
Add onion.
Cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Stir well.
Pour into 3-quart (13 x 9-inch) casserole dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream, melted butter, onion, cheese and salt.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix together corn flakes and melted butter; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: almost snickers
directions: Mix well, except for Grape-Nuts.
Pour in 8-inch square pan and top with Grape-Nuts.
Freeze and cut into 8 pieces.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix eggs, soup, mayo, grated cheese and onion.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Layer broccoli on bottom of baking dish (9 x 13-inch), then pour mixture over broccoli.
In frying pan, melt 1 cube butter.
Smash Ritz crackers until crumbs and fry in butter until golden.
Spread crackers on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (no cover).

title: zucchini pie(tastes like apple)
directions: Peel and cut zucchini lengthwise; remove seeds.
Slice and steam-cook until tender.
Place in ice water for 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix all other ingredients together, then pour over squash slices, mixing together well.
Put mixture into a 9-inch pie shell. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until crust is golden.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Boil for a few seconds.
Add jello.
Set until cool in
1-quart mold.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Arrange one layer of tomato slices in the bottom of a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine sugar, salt and pepper, mixing well. Sprinkle tomatoes with about 1/3 each of sugar mixture, bread crumbs and cheese. Repeat layers of tomato slices, sugar mixture and bread crumbs (omit the cheese). Dot with butter or margarine over the top of casserole. Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour. Add remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together sausage and flour.
Add grated cheese; mix well. Roll into balls and bake on large cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth. Add the sugar and mix well. Add the Cool Whip and mix well. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: buckeyes
directions: Line baking sheet with wax paper.
In bowl, mix peanut butter, vanilla, powdered sugar and butter.
Using 1 heaping tablespoonful, shape into balls with hands.
Dough will be stiff.
Place balls on wax paper and chill.
Melt shortening and chocolate chips in small bowl or cup over hot water.
Remove from heat; make sure chocolate is lump free.
Using a toothpick, dip each chilled ball into chocolate about 3/4 to top, leaving the "eye" clear.
Return to wax paper and chill again.
Store between layers of waxed paper in tightly covered container.
Makes 60 candies at 89 calories each. (As in the buckeye state of Ohio, these resemble the "eye" of an opened chestnut.)

title: cheese stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers.
Hollow out centers.
Mix all ingredients; stuff.
Bake until tender.

title: krazy kake
directions: Get your cake pan out and do not grease it.
In your cake pan, sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Make 3 indentations and put in each one the vanilla, vinegar and salad oil.
Then add water.
Mix all in the cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nut cups
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and flour; shape into 24 balls and press into small tins.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour equally into nut cups.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 250° and bake 10 minutes more. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: creole beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; add onion, green pepper and garlic. Boil 1/2 hour, then lower to simmer.
Cook sausage in a bit of water 15 minutes to draw out most of the fat.
Add to beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Slowly cook for 2 or 3 hours.
Add water if needed.
If you want real thick gravy, crush lots of beans after they begin to fall apart.
Serve over rice.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add mixed vegetables and tomato sauce to ground beef.
Add water.
Mix cornbread mix according to the directions.
Pour over the top of the mixture and bake in the oven until the corn bread is ready.
(Best if cooked in an iron skillet.)

title: strawberry iced tea fizz
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Let steep 5 minutes. Remove bags and cool.
Add strawberries and lemonade concentrate; chill.
Add club soda, chilled.
Serve with ice cubes.
Makes 2 gallons (24 servings).

title: ginger marble cake(makes 18 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 3 1/2-inch tube pan.
Prepare pound cake mix.
Set aside.
Prepare gingerbread mix, using only 3/4 cup water.
Spoon white and brown batters alternately into pan.
Cut through batter once with spatula.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes.
Turn out on rack and let cool.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs and butter well.
Slowly mix in self-rising flour, then add vanilla and nuts.
Put in a large pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° until done, around an hour.

title: ham and chicken casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
In a large bowl, combine ham, chicken, peppers, olives, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and onion.
Fold in noodles.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Yield: 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Mix zucchini, sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Loosen sides of loaves; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
Wrap tightly and store at room temperature up to 4 days or refrigerate up to 10 days.
Makes 2 loaves, 24 slices each. Contains 95 calories per slice.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all together in large punch bowl.
Enjoy.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients except coconut in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into a 9-inch deep dish pie pan.
Top with coconut.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and chop.
Add party dip and lemon juice. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Layer hash browns on bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix together cream of chicken, cream of celery, sour cream, onion and cheese and pour over hash brown patties.
Melt oleo and add corn flakes. Sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: super salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours. Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: creole salad dressing
directions: Combine dressing with remaining ingredients.
Mix well just before using.

title: crunch cereal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oil, butter, egg and vanilla. Add the rest of the ingredients. Roll in balls and press with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Spread over first layer and bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (according to oven watts of electricity).

title: lemonade
directions: Pour water into clear plastic glass.
Add sugar or honey to water.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour solution into paper cup.
Add lemon juice to cup.
Add ice cube.
Stir and enjoy! M-M Good!

title: health drink
directions: Blend well.
Blend 3 teaspoons of mixture and add to 8 ounces of distilled water.
Drink 3 glasses a day.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix Bisquick, cheese and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs until moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
Fry in butter, oleo or oil.
(No stick skillet - spray with oil).
Drizzle with syrup or honey to taste (optional).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil and sugar; mix well.
Then add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Mix these well and then add grated zucchini, raisins, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Beat well.
Grease the loaf pans.
Fill and bake 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: southern coffee punch
directions: Combine cold coffee, milk, vanilla and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Chill thoroughly.
At serving time, pour ice cream in punch bowl and top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add other ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Use spoon, not a mixer.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool in pan, then frost.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion, pepper, garlic powder, sour cream and dried beef in small baking dish.
Saute pecans in butter and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Fry, brown and drain hamburger, onions and bacon.
Add to the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until thick. Combine sausage, corn and sauce.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly or top is slightly browned.

title: frozen salad(serves 7)
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add fruit cocktail and maraschino cherries.
Mix well.
Pour into a freezing tray. Place in freezer.
When frozen, keep wax paper over salad.
Just before serving, remove from freezer and cut; place on lettuce lined plate.

title: oh so good bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Pour into large greased cookie sheet.
Lightly sprinkle flour on top and on hands and pat into pan.
Pour condensed sweetened milk over the top. Spread Heath chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown or bubbly.

title: marzipan loaves
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat butter and almond paste; beat in sugar until light, then beat in eggs. With mixer on low, add flour and milk, alternating.
Divide among pans (sprayed with cooking spray).
Sprinkle with almonds and sugar.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 (4 1/2 x 2-inch) loaves.

title: company chili
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage and onion in a Dutch oven. Cook until beef is browned, stirring to crumble; drain. Drain pinto beans. Add liquid to Dutch oven. Stir in remaining ingredients except beans. Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Stir in beans. Cook an additional 15 minutes. Yields about 3 quarts.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Sprinkle roast with garlic and pepper.
Roast at 350° until medium-rare.
Drain and reserve drippings.
Cool several hours or overnight.
Slice as thinly as possible.
In saucepan, blend drippings and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add sliced beef.
Cool and place in refrigerator, covered (I use a heavy-duty Ziploc bag), for 2 to 4 days.
Spoon liquid over meat frequently or turn Ziploc bag often. To serve, heat and serve on poor boy buns.
Use marinade to dip sandwiches in.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems of mushrooms and save.
Brush clean caps with butter and place in baking dish.
Saute sausage and onions until lightly browned.
Drain.
Add sherry and simmer until liquid is gone.
Add remainder of ingredients, chopped stems.
Add enough cream for mixture to be moist, but hold its shape in a spoon. Fill caps and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: saucy pot roast
directions: In heavy pot brown roast in hot oil.
Combine water, broth, tomato sauce, onions, sugar, vinegar, salt, cinnamon, bay leaf, pepper and ginger.
Pour this over meat and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cover and simmer until meat is tender (2 1/2 to 3 hours).
Remove meat and discard bay leaf.

title: chocolate and peanut butter truffles(makes about 3 dozen)
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with butter. Stir in cocoa until smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk and vanilla; cook and stir until thickened and well blended, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Chill 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in any of the listed coatings.
Chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: chicken or crab salad indienne
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Several hours before serving, combine rice with cooked chicken (or crab meat), celery, pepper, bacon and raisins.
Make dressing of curry powder, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Blend 3/4 dressing into salad.
Chill. Serve on crisp greens and top with remaining dressing.
Serve with coconut, nuts and chutney, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: shrimp and vegetables
directions: In skillet heat margarine until bubbly and hot; saute mushrooms and onion.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp turns pink.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice, and stir to combine.
Continue cooking until mixture is heated through, about 5 minutes.
Transfer shrimp mixture to serving platter.
Arrange rice in circle around shrimp mixture.
Yield:
2 servings.
Carbohydrate 46 g, protein 35 g, fat 15 g, calories 467.
One serving = 3 protein exchange, 1 bread exchange, 3 1/2 vegetable exchange, 1 1/2 fat exchange.

title: butterscotch oaties
directions: Melt morsels and oleo in double boiler.
Remove from heat. Add boiling water and baking soda.
Gradually blend in oats, flour, sugar and salt.
Dough will be stiff after mixed well. Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto sprayed cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: matrimonial fruit cake
directions: Cut up dates and boil with water and brown sugar.
Let cool. Mix flour with soda.
Add brown sugar, oatmeal and butter.
Cream all together and pack half on bottom of greased 10 x 7-inch pan. Spoon date mixture over this and cover with rest of crumbs. Sprinkle with small amount of oatmeal.
Bake slowly at 300° for 30 minutes or until set.
This is a nice holiday recipe that keeps well.

title: barbecued chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle both sides of roast with MSG.
Place in shallow baking dish. Thoroughly combine remainder of ingredients. Pour mixture over roast and marinate for 2 to 3 hours, turning once or twice (may be marinated longer, if desired).
Place roast on grill and broil about 6-inches from heat. Turn roast and baste with marinade every 10 to 15 minutes.
Broil for a total of 35 to 45 minutes for medium-rare or until desired doneness.

title: sugar-free brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir until blended.
Turn into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
One 2-inch square equals 95 calories.

title: trifle
directions: Prepare pudding with milk and chill.
Line large glass bowl with pound cake slices.
Sprinkle slices with the orange liqueur. Top with peach slices.
Reserve 1 cup Cool Whip.
Fold remaining Cool Whip into chilled pudding.
Continue layering until bowl is almost filled, ending with pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip, garnishing with sliced almonds or a few slices of peaches.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Mix sugar, butter, water and peppermint.
Make into patties. Stick toothpicks into each and let set.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Dip each pattie in mixture.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Peel onions and cook in salted water for 15 minutes until just tender.
Place in baking dish.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add flour and blend until smooth, cooking 3 minutes.
Heat milk and slowly stir into flour mixture.
Bring just to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly with a wire whip.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add pimento and parsley.
Pour over onions.
Mix crumbs with softened butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: salmon mousse(nice for parties and receptions.)
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Add water, if necessary, to equal 1/2 cup liquid.
Bone and finely flake salmon; set aside. Combine gelatin and liquid in a heat proof cup.
Place container in a pan of hot water and stir gelatin mixture to dissolve.
Transfer gelatin to mixing bowl and blend in mayonnaise.
Stir in chili sauce, lemon juice, Worcestershire, dill weed and pepper.
Fold in flaked salmon, tuna, egg, chopped olives (optional) and onion.

title: chocolate flavored chip cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, salt and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: southern peach cobbler
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, adding evaporated milk and vanilla. Blend until smooth.
In 350° oven, place butter in 8 x 11-inch pan until melted; add peaches with juice.
Pour batter over top and cook for approximately 1 hour or until dough is relatively firm. Remove and allow to cool for 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: In uncooked pie crust, place onion, bacon and cheese.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, milk and seasoning and pour on top.
Place in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix the pineapple and pudding.
Then add Cool Whip and marshmallows and then fold in the chopped walnuts.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Stir in chocolate morsels.

title: sotterley chicken(a plantation near st. mary's, maryland.)
directions: Combine ingredients and place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put in refrigerator a few hours or overnight.
Top with buttered bread crumb (2 slices bread).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Heat water and sugar together until sugar melts; let cool. Mix the flour, nutmeg, Crisco and baking powder.
Mix until texture of corn meal.
Add sugar-water mixture and mix well.
Roll very thin.
Cut into desired shapes; dip in sugar and place on a pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple nut pie
directions: Peel apples and cut into eighths.
In saucepan, mix sugar, cinnamon and water.
Add apples.
Toss lightly to coat with sugar mixture.
Place over medium heat and cook until slices are half done, about 10 minutes.
Arrange apples in greased 9-inch deep dish pie pan and pour syrup over them.
Cream butter with brown sugar. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Work in creamed mixture with wooden spoon, them mix in nuts.
Sprinkle over apples in pan to cover top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is a delicate brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or plain.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook until consistency of gravy.
Bake roast; cool.
Pull apart into pieces and put into sauce.
Stir. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: orange sherbet jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet and mix well. When partially set, fold Cool Whip into jello, gradually.
Add cut mandarin oranges.
Chill until firm.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Brown meats together and drain fat.
Add Velveeta, stir until melted.
Season to taste.
Place spoonfuls on party beads and broil in oven.

title: chicken la orange
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika. Roll pieces in flour.
Place chicken in casserole.
Sprinkle over with onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
In saucepan, mix orange juice, sherry, brown sugar, salt and orange rind.
Mix water and cornstarch.
Stir into orange juice mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture thickens.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to box.
Mix in cream cheese.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Layer in 8 to 10-inch dish cookies, pudding, cookies, pudding, etc.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender.
Drain and place in a casserole dish.
Add margarine and Velveeta, salt and pepper. Stir well.
Top with crumbled saltines and dot with margarine (approximately 1/2 cup).
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts and crackers brown on top.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine (or butter) in large saucepan over low heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Use fresh marshmallows for best results.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Transfer to large baking dish.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Top with 1/2 cup sliced almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: low-fat meat loaf muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Press into muffin pans.
Spray with Pam. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and pepper; cook until tender. Add cooked rice in skillet with ground beef.
Add soup and tomato sauce; heat.
Sprinkle cheese on top and serve when melted.

title: jerry's jambalaya
directions: Get dough.
Pat it out.
Roll it.
Put the cookie cutters in. Bake it.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 1-quart casserole dish and sprinkle lemon juice over the apples.
Microwave apples and lemon juice on High until apples are tender and crisp, about 2 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Set apples aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl and microwave on High until bubbly, about 1 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes. Stir after half of cooking time.
Spread the ingredients over the apples and place back in the microwave.
Cook on High until apples are tender and the ingredients on top of apples are bubbly, about 4 to 6 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yam ham apple casserole
directions: Cook apple pie slices according to label directions.
Drain yams and apple slices; combine the liquids.
Add salt and butter and stir well.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Arrange layers of yams, apple slices and ham in greased casserole or pans.
Pour syrup over layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Can also pour marshmallows over the layers.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
Split both layers horizontally after they have cooled.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a large greased dish.
Crush cornflakes and sprinkle on top.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Slice tops off tomatoes.
Scoop out inside, invert and drain. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Fill tomatoes with mixture and serve or chill up to 8 hours.
Garnish with crushed bacon or extra chives.

title: chicken chinese noodle casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange 1/2 noodles in layers. Blend soup and milk, then add remaining ingredients.
Spoon chicken mixture over noodles; top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Add flour, baking powder and soda and then the bananas.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast sweet bread
directions: Cut sweet bread into slices.
Spread margarine on both sides and place on a hot grill or frypan.
Cook until brown.
Flip and cook other side.
Bring to the table and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine and shape into 2 cheese balls.
Refrigerate.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: steve's world famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar,
brown
sugar,
eggs and softened margarine; beat well.
Add	flour,	baking powder, baking soda and a dash of salt; mix
well.	Stir
in oats, coconut, nuts and raisins. Put dough in refrigerator for 15 to 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Place flattened dough drops 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Put
dough	back
in refrigerator while baking. Sprinkle cinnamon on top of dough and bake for 8 to 11 minutes or until golden brown, do not overcook!

title: egg and string bean casserole
directions: Cook beans.
Brown onion lightly in butter.
Mix sliced eggs with beans.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour soup over all.
Sprinkle cheese and crumbs over top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 350°, about 50 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Boil chicken just until tender.
Let cool.
Cut into thin strips and then each strip into pieces about 1 to 1 1/2 inches long.
Using Bisquick or Jiffy mix, mix up 1 batch of pancake batter, but add extra milk to make the batter thin.
Put the chicken pieces in the batter and coat completely.

title: betty's crab dip
directions: Combine crab and lemon juice in double boiler. Add cream cheese and stir to melt.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Make 24 hours ahead and refrigerate.
Add mayonnaise to soften if desired.

title: crispy lemon baked chicken
directions: Combine lemon peel, juice and butter.
Separately combine crackers, onion powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in butter mixture.
Coat with crumb mixture.
Arrange on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 35 minutes or until tender.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, layer first 4 ingredients in the order they appear.
Cover with Hellmann's mayo mixed with the sugar.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.
To serve, toss and place in large salad bowl.
Top with grated sharp cheese.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the chili sauce and jelly and shape into 1 inch balls.
Brown meatballs in shortening.
Pour off grease.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly, stirring until melted. Add meatballs and stir until coated.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: munchy onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1/4-inch thick; separate into rings.
Soak in ice water 2 hours.
Drain and dry.
Mix other ingredients into a batter.
Dip onion rings in batter and fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake about 20 minutes at 375°.

title: treasure bars
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Put chili in a bowl, then add cream cheese.
Put grated cheese on top.
Put in microwave until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Beat eggs in large mixer bowl on high speed until foamy. Beat in flour and sugars. Beat in margarine. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Spoon into pie shell. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted 1/4 from edge comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.

title: fresh spinach with bacon
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet over medium-high heat.
Add spinach and saute until limp.
Add crumbled bacon and toss to combine.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peddler's soup
directions: Boil chicken.
When cooked, strain broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Return to broth.
Add cabbage.
When cabbage is almost done, add string beans, kidney beans and rice.
Add seasonings.
Simmer until done.

title: hamburger and squash
directions: Put ground chuck on bottom of large skillet and rest of ingredients over meat. Cook slowly on top of stove with lid just as you would fry potatoes. Stir and cook until vegetables are tender and meat is brown.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion.
Combine with salt and allow to set for 2 hours.
Rinse with cold water.
